obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31861)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31861&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Forest Act, 1927.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India except the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States.`
  line
  line `(3) It applies to the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in`
  line `the States of Bihar, Bombay, Coorg, Delhi, Madhya Pradesh, Orissa, Punjab, Uttar Pradesh and West`
  line `Bengal; but the Government of any State may by notification in the Official Gazette bring this Act into`
  line `force^2 in the whole or any specified part of that State to which this Act extends and where it is not in`
  line force.]
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 1 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 1 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 (XVI of`
  line `1927), in its application to the whole of the State of Maharashtra as provided by section 2 (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as "the principal Act"),--`
  line
  line `(i) to sub-section (2), after the words and letter "Part B States", the words "other than the`
  line `Hyderabad area of the State of Maharashtra" shall be added;`
  line
  line `(ii) to sub-section (3), the following proviso shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that, on the commencement of the Indian Forest (Maharashtra Unification and`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1960 (Mah. VI of 1961), this Act shall be in force in the Hyderabad area of the`
  line `State of Maharashtra."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for sub-sections (2) and (3).`
  line
  line `2. This Act has beed declared to be in force in the Khondmals District by the Khondmals laws regulations, 1936 (4 of 1936), s. 3 and the`
  line `Schedule.; and in the Angul District by the Angul Laws Regulation, 1936 (5 of 1936), and the Schedule. This Act has been extended in`
  line `its application to:--`
  line
  line `(1) Berar (partially) by the Berar Laws Act, 1941 (4 of 1941);`
  line
  line `(2) The Province of Coorg, see Coorg Gazette, 1930, Pt. I, p. 94;`
  line
  line `(3) The Delhi Province see Gazette of India, 1933, Pt. II-A, p. 293;`
  line
  line `(4) The whole of Madhya Pradesh by Madhya Pradesh Act 23 of 1958 (when notified);`
  line
  line `(5) Dadra and Nagar Haveli (w.e.t. 1-7-1965) by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(6) Pondicherry on 1-10-1963: vide Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3 and the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(7) Goa, Darnan and Diu by Reg. 11 of 1963, s. 3 and the Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(8) the whole of the Union territory of Lakshadweep (w.e.f. 1-10-1967): vide Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and the Schedule. The Act has`
  line `been repealed in its application to Bellary District by Mysore Act 14 of 1955.`
  line
  line `(9) Extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31862)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Interpretation clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31862&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context, --`
  line
  line `(1) "cattle" includes elephants, camels, buffaloes, horses, mares, geldings, ponies, colts, fillies,`
  line `mules, asses, pigs, rams, ewes, sheep, lambs, goats and kids;`
  line
  line `(2) "Forest-officer" means any person whom ^1*** the ^2[State Government] or any officer`
  line `empowered by ^1*** the ^2[State Government] in this behalf, may appoint to carry out all or any of the`
  line `purposes of this Act or to do anything required by this Act or any rule made there under to be done by`
  line `a Forest-officer;`
  line
  line `(3) "forest-offence" means an offence punishable under this Act or under any rule made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(4) "forest-produce" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the following whether found in, or brought from, a forest or not, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `timber, charcoal, caoutchouc, catechu, wood-oil, resin, natural varnish, bark, lac, mahua`
  line `flowers, mahua seeds ^3[, kuth] and myrabolams, and`
  line
  line `(b) the following when found in, or brought from, a forest, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(i) trees and leaves, flowers and fruits, and all other parts or produce not hereinbefore`
  line `mentioned, of trees,`
  line
  line `(ii) plants not being trees (including grass, creepers, reeds and moss), and all parts or`
  line `produce of such plants,`
  line
  line `(iii) wild animals and skins, tusks, horns, bones, silk, cocoons, honey and wax, and all`
  line `other parts or produce of animals, and`
  line
  line `(iv) peat, surface soil, rock, and minerals (including limestone, laterite, mineral oils, and`
  line `all products of mines or quarries);`
  line
  line `^4[(4A) "owner" includes a Court of Wards in respect of property under the superintendence or charge`
  line `of such Court;]`
  line
  line `(5) "river" includes any stream, canal, creek or other channels, natural or artifical;`
  line
  line `(6) "timber" includes trees when they have fallen or have been felled, and all wood whether cut up or`
  line `fashioned or hollowed out for any purpose or not; and`
  line
  line `(7) "tree" includes palms, ^5***, stumps, brush-wood and canes.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs)--`
  line
  line `(i) Section 2."for clause (1), the following clauses shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) "authorised officer" means an officer authorized under sub-section (2) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(1A) cattle include elephants, camels, buffaloes, horses, mares, geldings, ponies, colts, fillies, mules, asses, pigs, ram, ewes, sheep, lambs, goats and kids;`
  line
  line `(1B) "forest based industry" means an industry or unit in which any forest produce is used as raw material or as a source of energy.`
  line
  line `(ii) for clause (4), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:-`
  line
  line `(4) "forest-produce" include--`
  line
  line `(a) timber, charcoal, caoutchouc, catechu, wood-oil, resin, natural varnish, bark, lac, kuth, myrobalans, dioscorea, firewood, humus, rasaunt, morels (Morchella spp), Aconitum spp, Podophyllum spp, Picrorhizaspp, Trillium spp, Nardostachys spp, Taxus spp, Valerianassp, Rheum spp, wild animals, skins, tusks, horns, bones and all other parts or produce of wild animals whether found in, or brought from, a forest or not; and`
  line
  line `(b) the following when found in, or brought from, a forest, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) trees and leaves, flowers and fruits, roots and all other parts or produce of trees not specified in clause (a);`
  line
  line `(ii) plants not being trees (including grass, bamboos, creepers, reeds and moss and lichen), and all parts or produce of such plants;`
  line
  line `(iii) silk, cocoons, honey and wax; and`
  line
  line `(iv) peat, surface soil, rock, and minerals (including limestone, laterite, mineral oils, and all products of mines or quarries).`
  line
  line `(iii) after clause (5), insert the following clause, namely:-`
  line
  line `(5A) "saw mill" means any plant and machinery with which and the premises (including the precincts thereof) in which or in any part of which sawing is carried on with the aid of electrical or mechanical power.`
  line
  line `(iv) after clause (6), insert the following clause, namely:-`
  line
  line `(6A) "transporter" includes a person, a private agency, a Government Department, Corporation or any other agency engaged in transport of forest produce whether on his own or on behalf of any other person;`
  line
  line `(v) after clause (7), insert the following clause;`
  line
  line `(8) "wild animal" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2. --In section 2 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) In clause (4)--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-clause (a), for the words "and myrobolams", the words "myrobolams, gum,`
  line `sal seeds, sal leaves, kendu leaves, wild animals, skins, tusks, horns and bones, and all other`
  line `parts of produce of wild animals" shall be substituted ;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-clause (b), in item (iii), the words "Wild animals and skins tusks, horns and`
  line `bones" and the words "and all other parts or produce of animals" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (7), the following clause shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(8) wild animals shall have same meaning as defined in the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972.]`
  line
  line `[Vide the Tripura Act 10 of 1984, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act no. XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927,`
  line `hereinafter referred to as the principal Act, for clause (1) the following clause shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) "authorised officer" means an officer authorised under sub-section (1) of section 52-A;`
  line
  line `(1-A) "cattle" includes elephants, camels, buffaloes, horses, mares, geldings, ponies, colts, fillies,`
  line `mules, asses, pigs, rams, ewes, sheep, lambs, goats and kids;"`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act no. XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of Indian Forest Act, 1927,`
  line `hereinafter referred to as the principal Act, the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `2-A. "authorised officer" means an officer authorised under sub-section (1) of section 52-A.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttaranchal Act 10 of 2002, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, in subclause (4), after the words "tamborni leaves" the words "rosha grass, rauwolfia serpentine" shall be`
  line inserted.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XVII of 1956, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as "the said Act"), in sub-clause (a) of clause (4), after the word "kuth" the words`
  line `", apta and temburni leaves" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXIV of 1955, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, in its`
  line `application to the State of Maharashtra, in sub-clause (a) of clause (4), for the words", rosha grans,`
  line `rauwolfia serpentine" the words "rosha grass including oil derived therefrom, ranwolfia serpentine" shall`
  line `be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XXVII of 1968, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the principal act, after clause (4A),`
  line `the following clauses shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(4B) "Police Officer" means a Police Officer defined in the Bombay Police Act, 1951;`
  line
  line `(4C) Revenue Officer means a Revenue Officer as defined in the Bombay Land Revenue Code,`
  line `1879, or where that Code is not in force, as defined in a law corresponding to that Code;`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 2A in Act XVI of 1927.--After section 2 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"2A. Construction of certain references to Central or Bombay Acts.--In the application of this`
  line `Act to any area of the State of Maharashtra other than the Bombay area thereof, any reference to a`
  line `provision of a Central or Bombay Act shall, where no such Act is in force in that area, be construed as`
  line `a reference to the provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 5]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 2 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, in its`
  line `application to the State of Maharashtra (hereinafter referred to as "the principal Act"), of In clause (4C), for the words and figures "the Bombay Land Revenue Code, 1879 (Bom. V of 1879), or, where that Code`
  line `is not in force, as defined in a law corresponding to that Code;" the words and figures "the Maharashtra`
  line `Land Revenue Code, 1966 (Mah. XLI of 1966)" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the G.G. in C. or" rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1930, s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1933, s. 2.`
  line
  line `5. The word "bamboos" omitted by Act 5 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f 23-11-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31863)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to reserve forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31863&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government[ may constitute any forest-land or waste-land`
  line `which is the property of Government, or over which the Government has proprietary rights, or to the`
  line `whole or any part of the forest-produce of which the Government is entitled, a reserved forest in the`
  line `manner hereinafter provided.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 3 of Act XVI of 1927.--For section 3 of the Indian Forest Act,`
  line `1927 (hereinafter called the principal Act), the following shall be substituted namely--`
  line
  line `"Powers to reserve forests.--The State Government may constitute any forest land or any other`
  line `land (not being land for the time being comprised in any holding or in any village abadi) which is the`
  line `property of Government or over which the Government has proprietary rights, or to the whole or any`
  line `part of the forest produce of which the Government is entitled, a reserve forest in the manner`
  line `hereinafter provided.`
  line
  line `Explanation-- The expression 'holding' shall have the meaning assigned to it in the U.P. Tenancy`
  line `Act, 1939, and the expression 'village abadi' shall have the meaning assigned to it in the U.P. Village`
  line `Abadi Act, 1947."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act, XXIII of 1965, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31864)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Notification by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31864&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it has been decided to constitute any land a`
  line `reserved forest, the ^1[State Government] shall issue a notification in the ^2[Official Gazette]--`
  line
  line `(a) declaring that it has been decided to constitute such land a reserved forest;`
  line
  line `(b) specifying, as nearly as possible, the situation and limits of such land; and`
  line
  line `(c) appointing an officer (hereinafter called "the Forest Settlement-officer") to inquire into and`
  line `determine the existence, nature and extent of any rights alleged to exist in favour of any person in or`
  line `over any land comprised within such limits, or in or over any forest-produce, and to deal with the`
  line `same as provided in this Chapter.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of clause (b), it shall be sufficient to describe the limits of the forest`
  line `by roads, rivers, ridges or other well-known or readily intelligible boundaries.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer appointed under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall ordinarily be a person not holding`
  line `any forest-office except that of Forest Settlement-officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall prevent the ^3[State Government] from appointing any number of`
  line `officers not exceeding three, not more than one of whom shall be a person holding any forest-office`
  line `except as aforesaid, to perform the duties of a Forest Settlement-officer under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31865)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Bar of accrual of forest-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31865&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `After the issue of a notification under section 4, no right shall be`
  line `acquired in or over the land comprised in such notification, except by succession or under a grant or`
  line `contract in writing made or entered into by or on behalf of the Government or some person in whom such`
  line `right was vested when the notification was issued; and no fresh clearings for cultivation or for any other`
  line `purpose shall be made in such land except in accordance with such rules as may be made by the ^1[State`
  line `Government] in this behalf.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 5.--For section 5 of the principal Act, the following shall be`
  line `substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"5. Bar of accrual of forest rights.--After the issue of a notification under section 4, no right shall`
  line `be acquired in or over the land comprised in such notification, except by succession or under a grant or`
  line `contract in writing made or entered into by or on behalf of the Government or some person in whom such`
  line `right was vested when the notification was issued; and no fresh clearings for cultivation or for any other`
  line `purpose shall be made in such land nor any tree therein felled, girdled, lopped, tapped, or burnt, or its`
  line `bark or leaves tripped off, or the same otherwise damaged, nor any forest-produce removed therefrom,`
  line `except in accordance with such rules as may be made by the State Government in this behalf."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31866)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Proclamation by Forest Settlement-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31866&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `When a notification has been issued under section`
  line `4, the Forest Settlement-officer shall publish in the local vernacular in every town and village in the`
  line `neighbourhood of the land comprised therein, a proclamation--`
  line
  line `(a) specifying, as nearly as possible, the situation and limits of the proposed forest;`
  line
  line `(b) explaining the consequences which, as hereinafter provided, will ensue on the reservation of`
  line `such forest; and`
  line
  line `(c) fixing a period of not less than three months from the date of such proclamation, and requiring`
  line `every person claiming any right mentioned in section 4 or section 5 within such period either to`
  line `present to the Forest Settlement-officer a written notice specifying or to appear before him and state,`
  line `the nature of such right and the amount and particulars of the compensation (if any) claimed in`
  line `respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31867)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Inquiry by Forest Settlement-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31867&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Forest Settlement-officer shall take down in writing`
  line `all statements made under section 6, and shall at some convenient place inquire into all claims duly`
  line `preferred under that section, and the existence of any rights mentioned in section 4 or section 5 and not`
  line `claimed under section 6 so far as the same may be ascertainable from the records of Government and the`
  line `evidence of any persons likely to be acquainted with the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31868)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers of Forest Settlement-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31868&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of such inquiry, the Forest Settlementofficer may exercise the following powers, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(a) power to enter, by himself or any officer authorised by him for the purpose, upon any land,`
  line `and to survey, demarcate and make a map of the same; and`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of a Civil Court in the trial of suits.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31869)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Extinction of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31869&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Rights in respect of which no claim has been preferred under section 6 and`
  line `of the existence of which no knowledge has been acquired by inquiry under section 7, shall be`
  line `extinguished, unless, before the notification under section 20 is published, the person claiming them`
  line `satisfies the Forest Settlement-officer that he had sufficient cause for not preferring such claim within the`
  line `period fixed under section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (31870)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Treatment of claims relating to practice of shifting cultivation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31870&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of a claim`
  line `relating to the practice of shifting cultivation, the Forest Settlement-officer shall record a statement setting`
  line `forth the particulars of the claim and of any local rule or order under which the practice is allowed or`
  line `regulated, and submit the statement to the State Government, together with his opinion as to whether the`
  line `practice should be permitted or prohibited wholly or in part.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the statement and opinion, the ^1[State Government] may make an order permitting or`
  line `prohibiting the practice wholly or in part.`
  line
  line `(3) If such practice is permitted wholly or in part, the Forest Settlement-officer may arrange for its`
  line exercise--
  line
  line `(a) by altering the limits of the land under settlement so as to exclude land of sufficient extent, of`
  line `a suitable kind, and in a locality reasonably convenient for the purposes of the claimants, or`
  line
  line `(b) by causing certain portions of the land under settlement to be separately demarcated, and`
  line `giving permission to the claimants to practice shifting cultivation therein under such conditions as he`
  line `may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(4) All arrangements made under sub-section (3) shall be subject to the previous sanction of the`
  line `^2[State Government].`
  line
  line `(5) The practice of shifting cultivation shall in all cases be deemed a privilege subject to control,`
  line `restriction and abolition by the ^2[State Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (31871)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to acquire land over which right is claimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31871&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of a claim to a right in or`
  line `over any land, other than a right-of-way or right of pasture, or a right to forest-produce or a watercourse,`
  line `the Forest Settlement-officer shall pass an order admitting or rejecting the same in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(2) If such claim is admitted in whole or in part, the Forest Settlement-officer shall either--`
  line
  line `(i) exclude such land from the limits of the proposed forest; or`
  line
  line `(ii) come to an agreement with the owner thereof for the surrender of his rights; or`
  line
  line `(iii) proceed to acquire such land in the manner provided by the Land Acquisition Act, 1894(1 of`
  line `1894).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of so acquiring such land--`
  line
  line `(a) the Forest Settlement-officer shall be deemed to be a Collector proceeding under the Land`
  line `Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  line
  line `(b) the claimant shall be deemed to be a person interested and appearing before him in pursuance`
  line `of a notice given under section 9 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the provisions of the preceding sections of that Act shall be deemed to have been complied`
  line `with; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Collector, with the consent of the claimant, or the Court, with the consent of both parties,`
  line `may award compensation in land, or partly in land and partly in money.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11.--In section 11 of the principal Act, after sub-section (3), the following`
  line `new sub-section shall be added, namely--`
  line
  line `"(4) The provisions of sub-section (3) shall apply also when the Forest Settlement Officer proceeds`
  line `to acquire any land in consequence of any order, passed on appeal or revision under this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (31872)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Order on claims to rights of pasture or to forest-produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31872&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a claim to rights of`
  line `pasture or to forest-produce, the Forest Settlement-officer shall pass an order admitting or rejecting the`
  line `same in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12 of Act XVI of 1927.--Section 12 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1)`
  line `of that section, and after the sub-section so renumbered, the following sub-section shall be inserted,`
  line `namely :--`
  line
  line `"(2) A copy of the order passed under sub-section (1) shall be furnished to the claimant by the`
  line `Forest Settlement Officer, and another copy of that order shall be forwarded to the Forest Officer who`
  line `attended the inquiry, or if no such Officer attended, to the Divisional Forest Officer.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (31873)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Record to be made by Forest Settlement-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31873&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Forest Settlement-officer, when passing`
  line `any order under section 12, shall record, so far as may be practicable,--`
  line
  line `(a) the name, father's name, caste, residence and occupation of the person claiming the right; and`
  line
  line `(b) the designation, position and area of all fields or groups of fields (if any), and the designation`
  line `and position of all buildings (if any) in respect of which the exercise of such rights is claimed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (31874)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Record where he admits claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31874&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If the Forest Settlement-officer admits in whole or in part any`
  line `claim under section 12, he shall also record the extent to which the claim is so admitted, specifying the`
  line `number and description of the cattle which the claimant is from time to time entitled to graze in the forest,`
  line `the season during which such pasture is permitted, the quantity of timber and other forest-produce which`
  line `he is from time to time authorised to take or receive, and such other particulars at; the case may require.`
  line `He shall also record whether the timber or other forest-produce obtained by the exercise of the rights`
  line `claimed may be sold or bartered.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (31875)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Exercise of rights admitted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31875&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) After making such record the Forest Settlement-officer shall,`
  line `to the best of his ability, and having due regard to the maintenance of the reserved forest in respect of`
  line `which the claim is made, pass such orders as will ensure the continued exercise of the rights so admitted.`
  line
  line `(2) For this purpose the Forest Settlement-officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) set out some other forest-tract of sufficient extent, and in a locality reasonably convenient, for`
  line `the purposes of such claimants, and record an order conferring upon them a right of pasture or to`
  line `forest-produce (as the case may be) to the extent so admitted; or`
  line
  line `(b) so alter the limits of the proposed forest as to exclude forest-land of sufficient extent, and in a`
  line `locality reasonably convenient, for the purposes of the claimants; or`
  line
  line `(c) record an order, continuing to such claimants a right of pasture or to forest-produce, as the`
  line `case may be, to the extent so admitted, at such seasons, within such portions of the proposed forest,`
  line `and under such rules, as may be made in this behalf by the ^1[State Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (31876)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Commutation of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31876&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `In case the Forest Settlement-officer finds it impossible, having due`
  line `regard to the maintenance of the reserved forest, to make such settlement under section 15 as shall ensure`
  line `the continued exercise of the said rights to the extent so admitted, he shall, subject to such rules as the`
  line `^1[State Government] may make in this behalf, commute such rights, by the payment to such persons of a`
  line `sum of money in lieu thereof, or by the grant of land, or in such other manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (31877)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appeal from order passed under section 11, section 12, section 15 or section 16.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31877&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `who has made a claim under this Act, or any Forest-officer or other person generally or specially`
  line `empowered by the ^1[State Government] in this behalf, may, within three months from the date of the`
  line `order passed on such claim by the Forest Settlement-officer under section 11, section 12, section 15 or`
  line `section 16, present an appeal from such order to such officer of the Revenue Department, of rank not`
  line `lower than that of a Collector, as the ^1[State Government] may, by notification in the ^2[Official Gazette],`
  line `appoint to hear appeals from such orders:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1[State Government] may establish a Court (hereinafter called the Forest Court)`
  line `composed of three persons to be appointed by the State Government, and, when the Forest Court has been`
  line `so established, all such appeals shall be presented to it.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 17.--For section 17 of the principal Act, the following shall`
  line `be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"Appeal from order passed under section 11, section 12, section 15 or section 16.--Any`
  line `person who has made a claim under this Act, or any Forest Officer or other person generally or`
  line `specially empowered by the State Government in this behalf may, within three months from the date`
  line `of the order passed on such claim by the Forest Settlement Officer under section 11, section 12,`
  line `section 15 or section 16, present an appeal from such order to the District Judge.`
  line
  line `Explanation-- In this section and in the succeeding sections of this Chapter. 'District Judge' means`
  line `the District Judge of the district in which the land is situate, and includes an Additional Districts`
  line `Judge to whom an appeal is transferred by the District Judge."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (31878)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appeal under section 17.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31878&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every appeal under section 17 shall be made by petition in`
  line `writing, and may be delivered to the Forest Settlement-officer, who shall forward it without delay to the`
  line `authority competent to hear the same.`
  line
  line `(2) If the appeal be to an officer appointed under section 17, it shall be heard in the manner prescribed`
  line `for the time being for the hearing of appeals in matters relating to land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) If the appeal be to the Forest Court, the Court shall fix a day and a convenient place in the`
  line `neighbourhood of the proposed forest for hearing the appeal, and shall give notice thereof to the parties`
  line `and shall hear such appeal accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) The order passed on the appeal by such officer or Court, or by the majority of the members of`
  line `such Court, as the case may be, shall, subject only to revision by the ^1[State Government], be final.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 18.--For section 18 of the principal Act, the following shall`
  line `be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"18. Appeal under section 17.--(1) Every appeal under section 17 shall be made by or in`
  line `writing and may be delivered to the Forest Settlement Officer, who shall forward it without delay to`
  line `the District Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Judge may, after giving to the parties an opportunity of being heard, confirm, set`
  line `aside or modify the order under appeal or remand the case to the Forest Settlement Officer with such`
  line `direction as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) During the pendency of the appeal the District Judge may, for sufficient cause, stay, on such`
  line `terms, if any, as he thinks fit, the operation of the order appealed from and pass any incidental or`
  line `consequential order.`
  line
  line `(4) The order passed on the appeal shall, subject to the provisions of section 22, be final."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (31879)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Pleaders.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31879&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government], or any person who has made a claim under this Act, may`
  line `appoint any person to appear, plead and act on its or his behalf before the Forest Settlement-officer, or the`
  line `appellate officer or Court, in the course of any inquiry or appeal under this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 19.--For section 19 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `shall be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"19. Pleaders.--The State Government, or any person who has made a claim under this Act,`
  line `may appoint any person to appear, plead and act on its or his behalf before the Forest Settlement`
  line `Officer or the District Judge in the course of any inquiry or appeal under this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (31880)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Notification declaring forest reserved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31880&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the following events have occurred,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the period fixed under section 6 for preferring claims has elapsed, and all claims, if any, made`
  line `under that section or section 9 have been disposed of by the Forest Settlement-officer;`
  line
  line `(b) if any such claims have been made, the period limited by section 17 for appealing from the`
  line `orders passed on such claims has elapsed, and all appeals (if any) presented within such period have`
  line `been disposed of by the appellate officer or Court; and`
  line
  line `(c) all lands (if any) to be included in the proposed forest, which the Forest Settlement-officer`
  line `has, under section 11 elected to acquire under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), have`
  line `become vested in the Government under section 16 of that Act.`
  line
  line `the ^1[State Government] shall publish a notification in the ^2[Official Gazette], specifying definitely,`
  line `according to boundary-marks erected or otherwise, the limits of the forest which is to be reserved, and`
  line `declaring the same to be reserved from a date fixed by the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date so fixed such forest shall be deemed to be a reserved forest.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 20A.-- After section 20, insert the following section--`
  line
  line `20A. Demarcated forests deemed to be reserved forests.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, any forest which has been notified as a demarcated forest under the erstwhile Jammu and Kashmir Forest Act, 1987 (1930 A.D.), prior to the appointed day notified under the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization Act, 2019, shall be deemed to be a reserved forest under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All questions decided, orders issued and records prepared in connection with the constitution of such forest as demarcated forests shall be deemed to have been decided, issued and prepared under this Act, and the provisions of this Act relating to reserved forests shall apply to forest to which the provision of sub-section (1) are applicable.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No.`
  line `S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws)`
  line `Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section after section 20, (16 of 1927).--After section 20 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927`
  line `(16 of 1927) (hereinafter referred to as the said Act), the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `20-A. Forest land or waste land deemed to be reserved forests.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, any forest land or waste land in the`
  line `merged territories, which had been recognized by the Ruler or any merged State immediately before the date of`
  line `merger as a reserved forest in pursuance or any law, custom, rule, regulation, order or notification for the time`
  line `being in force or which has been dealt with as such in any administration report or in accordance with any`
  line `working plan, or register maintained and acted upon immediately before the said date and has been continued`
  line `to be so dealt with thereafter, shall be deemed to be reserved forests for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of any rule, order or notification under this Act, application to the area in question any`
  line `law, custom, rule, regulation, order or notification mentioned in sub-section (1) shall, anything in law to the`
  line `contrary notwithstanding, be deemed to be validly in force as if he same had the force and effect of rules,`
  line `orders and notifications made under the provisions of this Act and shall continue to so remain in force until`
  line `superseded, altered or modified in accordance therewith.`
  line
  line `(3) No report working plan, or register as aforesaid or any entry therein shall be questioned in any court of`
  line `law; provided that the State Government have duly certified that such report, working plan, or register had`
  line `been prepared under the authority of the said Ruler before the date of the merger and has been under the`
  line `authority of the State Government continued to be recognized, maintained or acted upon thereafter.`
  line
  line `(4) Forests recognized in the merged territories as khesra forests, village forests or protected forests, or`
  line `forests other than reserved forests, by whatever name designed or locally known, shall be deemed to be`
  line `protected forests within the meaning of this Act and provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) shall mutatis`
  line `mutandis apply.`
  line
  line `Explanation I- "Working plan" includes any plan, scheme, project, maps, drawings and lay-outs prepared`
  line `for the purpose of carrying out the operations in course of the working and management of forests.`
  line
  line `Explanation II- "Ruler" includes the Darbar administration prior to the date of the merger and "State`
  line `Government" includes the successor Government after the said date.".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 11 of 1954, s.2]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 20.--For clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 20 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following shall be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"(b) if any such claims have been made, the period limited by section 17 for appealing from the`
  line `orders passed on such claims has elapsed, and all appeals (if any) presented within such period have`
  line `been disposed of by the District Judge; and".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 8]`
  line
  line `Addition of new section 20-A-- After section 20 of the principal Act, the following new section`
  line `shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"20-A. Certain forest land or waste land when deemed to be reserved forest.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `including the Merged States (Laws) Act, 1949 or the U.P. Merged States (Application of Laws) Act,`
  line `1950, or any order issued thereunder, any forest land or waste land in a merged State which`
  line `immediately before the date of merger (hereinafter in this section referred to as the said date),-`
  line
  line `(a) awas deemed to be a reserved forest under any enactment in force in that State, or`
  line
  line `(b) was recognized or declared by the Ruler of such State as reserved forest under any law`
  line `(including any enactment, rule, regulation, order, notification, custom or usage having the force`
  line `of law) for the time being in force, or`
  line
  line `(c) was dealt with as a reserved forest in any administrative report or in accordance with any`
  line `working plan or register maintained and acted upon under the authority of the Ruler,`
  line `shall be deemed to be and since the said date to have continued to be a reserved forest subject to`
  line `the same rights or concession, if any, in favour of any person as were in force immediately before`
  line `the said date.`
  line
  line `Explanation I-- A certificate of the State Government or of any officer authorised in this behalf to`
  line `the effect that a report, working plan or register was maintained and acted upon under the authority of`
  line `the Ruler shall be conclusive evidence of the fact that it was so maintained and acted upon.`
  line
  line `Explanation II-- Any question as to the existence or extent of any right or concession referred to`
  line `in this sub-section shall be determined by the State Government, whose decision, given after such`
  line `enquiry, if any as it thinks fit shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation III-- 'Working plan' includes any plan, scheme, project, map, drawings and layouts`
  line `prepared, for the purpose of carrying out the operations in the course of the working and management`
  line `of forests.`
  line
  line `(2) No right shall be deemed to have been acquired on or after the said date in or over any land`
  line `mentioned in sub-section(I) except by succession or under a grant or contract in writing made or`
  line `entered into by or on behalf of the State Government or some person in whom such rights was vested`
  line `immediately before the said date and no fresh clearings since made for cultivation or for any other`
  line `purpose (except clearings made in accordance with any concessions granted by the Ruler and in force`
  line `immediately before the said date or in accordance with the rules made by the State Government in`
  line `this behalf since the said date) shall be recognized as or deemed to be lawful, anything contained in`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force notwithstanding.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may within five years from the commencement of the Indian Forest`
  line `(Uttar Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1965, revise any arrangement of the nature specified in section 22,`
  line `and pass any incidental or consequential order, including any direction to the effect that any of the`
  line `proceedings specified in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter be taken.`
  line
  line `(4) In relation to any land mentioned in sub-section (1), the references in sections 24 and 26-`
  line
  line `(a) to section 23 shall be construed as references to sub-section (2) ; and`
  line
  line `(b) to rights admitted, recorded or continued under section 14 or section 15 shall be construed`
  line `as references to rights of pasture or to forest produce admitted, recorded or continued in or under`
  line `the corresponding enactment, law or documents referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to any action that may be or may have been taken for ejectment, vacation of`
  line `encroachment or recovery of damages in respect of any unauthorised occupation of or trespass over`
  line `any land mentioned in sub-section (1), or for seizure, confiscation, disposal or release (on payment of`
  line `value or otherwise) of any forest produce in respect of which any forest offence has been committed`
  line `in relation to such land or of any tools, boats, carts, or cattle used in committing such offence, nothing`
  line `in this section shall be deemed to authorize the conviction of any person for any act done before the commencement of the Indian Forest (Uttar Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1965, which was not an`
  line `offence before such commencement."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965,s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (31881)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Publication of translation of such notification in neighbourhood of forest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31881&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Forestofficer shall, before the date fixed by such notification, cause a translation thereof into the local`
  line `vernacular to be published in every town and village in the neighbourhood of the forest.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (31882)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to revise arrangement made under section 15 or section 18.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31882&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government]`
  line `may, within five years from the publication of any notification under section 20. revise any arrangement`
  line `made under section 15 or section 18, and may for this purpose rescind or modify any order made under`
  line `section 15 or section 18, and direct that any one of the proceedings, specified in section 15 be taken in`
  line `lieu of any other of such proceedings, or that the rights admitted under section 12 be commuted under`
  line `section 16.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section 22-A in Act 16 of 1927.--After Section 22 as amended in its application to`
  line `Uttar Pradesh, hereinafter referred to as the principal Act, the following section shall be inserted and shall`
  line `be deemed to have been inserted with effect from November 23, 1960, namely: --`
  line
  line `"22-A. Power of revision in other cases.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 22,`
  line `the State Government may, either of its own motion or on a petition being made in that behalf, call`
  line `for the record of any appeal decided under section 18, and may confirm the order passed on such`
  line `appeal, or set it aside, or modify it, or remand the case to the Forest Settlement officer with such`
  line `directions as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No petition under this section may be made, after November 22, 1965, and the State`
  line `Government may not exercise any power under this section, after the said date."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 11 of 1973, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 22.--For section 22 of the principal Act, the following shall be`
  line `substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"22. Powers to revise arrangements made under section 15 or section 18.--The State`
  line `Government may, within five years from the publication of any notification under section 20, revise`
  line `any arrangement made under section 15 or on appeal under section 18. and may for this purpose`
  line `rescind or modify any order made under section 15 or section 18, and direct that any of the`
  line `proceedings specified in section 15 be taken in lieu of any other of such proceedings, or that the rights`
  line `admitted under section 12 be commuted under section 16."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965,s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (31883)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `No right acquired over reserved forest, except as here provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31883&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No right of any description`
  line `shall be acquired in or over a reserved forest except by succession or under a grant or contract in writing`
  line `made by or on behalf of the ^1[Government] or some person in whom such right was vested when the`
  line `notification under section 20 was issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (31884)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Rights not to be alienated without sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31884&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 23, no right continued under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 15 shall be alienated by way`
  line `of grant, sale, lease, mortgage or otherwise, without the sanction of the ^1[State Government]:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when any such right is appendant to any land or house, it may be sold or otherwise`
  line `alienated with such land or house.`
  line
  line `(2) No timber or other forest-produce obtained in exercise of any such right shall be sold or bartered`
  line `except to such extent as may have been admitted in the order recorded under section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (31885)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to stop ways and water-courses in reserved forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31885&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Forest-officer may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the ^1[State Government] or of any officer duly authorised by it in this behalf, stop`
  line `any public or private way or water-course in a reserved forest, provided that a substitute for the way or`
  line `water-course so stopped, which the ^1[State Government] deems to be reasonably convenient, already`
  line `exists, or has been provided or constructed by the Forest-officer in lieu thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (31886)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Acts prohibited in such forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31886&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who-`
  line
  line `(a) makes any fresh clearing prohibited by section 5, or`
  line
  line `(b) sets fire to a reserved forest, or, in contravention of any rules made by the ^1State Government in`
  line `this behalf, kindles any fire, or leaves any fire burning, in such manner as to endanger such a forest;`
  line `or who, in a reserved forest`
  line
  line `(c) kindles, keeps or carries any fire except at such seasons as the Forest-officer may notify in this`
  line behalf;
  line `^2* * * *`
  line
  line `(f) fells, girdles, lops, taps or burns any tree or strips off the bark or leaves from, or otherwise`
  line `damages, the same;`
  line
  line `(g) quarries stone, burns lime or charcoal, or collects, subjects to any manufacturing process, orremoves, any forest-produce;`
  line
  line `(h) clears or breaks up any land for cultivation or any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(i) in contravention of any rules made in this behalf by the ^1State Government hunts, shoots, fishes,`
  line `poisons water or sets traps or snares; or`
  line
  line `(j) in any area in which the Elephants Preservation Act, 1879 (6 of 1879), is not in force, kills or`
  line `catches elephants in contravention of any rules so made;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both, in addition to such compensation for damage done to the`
  line `forest as the convicting Court may direct to be paid.`
  line
  line `^3(1A) Any person who, in a reserved forest`
  line
  line `(a) trespasses or pastures cattle, or permits cattle to trespass shall be liable to penalty which may`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees, in addition to such compensation for damage done to the forest as`
  line `determined by a Forest-officer empowered under section 68;`
  line
  line `(b) causes any damage by negligence in felling any tree or cutting or dragging any timber shall be`
  line `liable to penalty which may extend to five thousand rupees, in addition to such compensation for`
  line `damage done to the forest as determined by a Forest-officer empowered under section 68.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit`
  line
  line `(a) any act done by permission in writing of the Forest-officer, or under any rule made by`
  line `the ^1State Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) the exercise of any right continued under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 15, or created`
  line `by grant or contract in writing made by or on behalf of the Government under section 23.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever fire is caused wilfully or by gross negligence in a reserved forest,`
  line `the ^1State Government may (notwithstanding that any penalty has been inflicted under this section)`
  line `direct that in such forest or any portion thereof the exercise of all rights of pasture or to forest-produce shall be suspended for such period as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Clause (d) and (e) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (31887)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to declare forest no longer reserved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31887&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] may, by`
  line `notification in the ^2[Official Gazette], direct that, from a date fixed by such notification, any forest or any`
  line `portion thereof reserved under this Act shall cease to be a reserved forest.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date so fixed, such forest or portion shall cease to be reserved; but the rights (if any)`
  line `which have been extinguished therein shall not revive in consequence of such cessation.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Addition of new section 27-A.--In Chapter II of the principal Act, after section 27, the`
  line `following new section shall be added, namely--`
  line
  line `"27-A. Finality of orders etc.--No act done, order made or certificate issued in exercise of`
  line `any power conferred by or under this Chapter shall, except as hereinbefore provided, be called in`
  line `question in any Court."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 12]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (31888)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Formation of village-forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31888&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] may assign to any villagecommunity the rights of Government to or over any land which has been constituted a reserved forest,`
  line `and may cancel such assignment. All forests so assigned shall be called village-forests.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[State Government] may make rules for regulating the management of village-forests,`
  line `prescribing the conditions under which the community to which any such assignment is made may be`
  line `provided with timber or other forest-produce or pasture, and their duties for the protection and`
  line `improvement of such forest.`
  line
  line `(3) All the provisions of this Act relating to reserved forests shall (so far as they are not inconsistent`
  line `with the rules so made) apply to village-forests.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs)--`
  line
  line `Section 28.--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the word "reserved forest", substitute the words "reserved forest or declared a protected forest or is a land which has been entered in settlement records as khalsa land";`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (3) after the words "reserved forests", insert the words "or protected forests, as the case may be".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020). and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 28 of Act XVI of 1927--In section 28 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh (Hereinafter called the principal Act):`
  line
  line `(1) in sub-section (1)`
  line
  line `(i) between the word "Forest" and the comma, the following shall be inserted:`
  line
  line `"or declared a protected forest or is a forest belonging to the Government."`
  line
  line `(ii) for the full stop occurring at the end, a comma shall be substituted and thereafter the`
  line `following words and full stop shall be added:`
  line
  line `"and, subject to the rules made under sub-section (2) all the provisions of this Act relating to`
  line `reserved forests, protected forests, or forests belonging to the Government, shall, as the case may be,`
  line `apply to them."`
  line
  line `(2) sub-section (3) shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 2. ]`
  line
  line Maharashtra--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 28 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 28 of the said Act, --`
  line
  line `(1) in sub-section (1), after the word "village community" the words and figures "village`
  line `panchayat established under the Bombay Village Panchayats Act, 1933 (Bom. VI of 1933), or cooperative society registered or deemed to be registered under the Bombay Co-operative Societies act,`
  line `1925 (Bom. VII of 1925)," shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(2) in sub-section (2), after the word "community" the words ",panchayat or society" shall be`
  line inserted.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXIV of 1955, s. 3]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 28 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 28 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words and figures "the Bombay Village Panchayats Act, 1933 (Bom. VI of 1933)," the`
  line `words and figures "the Bombay Village Panchayats Act, 1958 (Bom. III of 1959)," shall be substituted.`
  line `(b) For the words and figures "the Bombay Co-operative Societies Act, 1925 (Bom. VII of 1925),"`
  line `the words and figures "the Maharashtra Societies Act, 1960 (Mah. XXIV of 1961)," shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (31889)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protected forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31889&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] may, by notification in the ^2[Official Gazette],`
  line `declare the provisions of this Chapter applicable to any forest-land or waste-land which is not included in a reserved forest, but which is the property of Government, or over which the Government has proprietary`
  line `rights, or to the whole or any part of the forests produce of which the Government is entitled.`
  line
  line `(2) The forest-land and waste-lands comprised in any such notification shall be called a protected`
  line forests.
  line
  line `(3) No such notification shall be made unless the nature and extent of the rights of Government and of`
  line `private persons in or over the forest-land or waste-land comprisedtherein have been inquired into and`
  line `recorded at a survey or settlement, or in such other manner as the ^3[State Government] thinks sufficient.`
  line
  line `Every such record shall be presumed to be correct until the contrary is proved:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if, in the case of any forest-land or waste-land, the ^3[State Government] thinks that`
  line `such inquiry and record are necessary, but that they will occupy such length of time as in the mean time to`
  line `endanger the rights of Government, the ^3[State Government] may, pending such inquiry and record,`
  line `declare such land to be a protected forest, but so as not to abridge or affect any existing rights of`
  line `individuals or communities.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 29A.- After section 29, insert the following section-`
  line
  line `29A. Undemarcated forests deemed to be protected forests.- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, any undemarcated forest (which means and includes all forest land other than demarcated forest which is the property of the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and is not appropriated for any specific purpose and includes all the undemarcated and berun line forest vested in the Forest Department under the provisions of section 48 of the Jammu and Kashmir Village Panchayat Act, 1958 or any other law for the time being in force), prior to the appointed day notified under the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization Act, 2019, shall be deemed to be a protected forest under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All questions decided, orders issued and records prepared in connection with the constitution of such forest as undemarcated forests shall be deemed to have been decided, issued and prepared under this Act, and the provisions of this Act relating to protected forests shall apply to forest to which the provision of sub-section (1) are applicable.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid, for "Local Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (31890)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to issue notification reserving trees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31890&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] may, by notification`
  line `in the ^19[Official Gazette],--`
  line
  line `(a) declare any trees or class of trees in a protected forests to be reserved from a date fixed by the`
  line notification;
  line
  line `(b) declare that any portion of such forest specified in the notification shall be closed for such`
  line `term, not exceeding thirty years, as the ^1[State Government] thinks fit, and that the rights of private`
  line `persons, if any, over such portion shall be suspended during such term, provided that the remainder of`
  line `such forest be sufficient, and in a locality reasonably convenient, for the due exercise of the rights`
  line `suspended in the portion so closed; or`
  line
  line `(c) prohibit, from a date fixed as aforesaid, the quarrying of stone, or the burning of lime or`
  line `charcoal, or the collection or subjection to any manufacturing process, or removal of, any forestproduce in any such forest, and the breaking up or clearing for cultivation, for building, for herding`
  line `cattle or for any other purpose, of any land in any such forest.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (31891)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Publication of translation of such notification in neighbourhood.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31891&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Collector shall cause a`
  line `translation into the local vernacular of every notification issued under section 30 to be affixed in a`
  line `conspicuous place in every town and village in the neighbourhood of the forests comprised in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (31892)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules for protected forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31892&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] may make rules to`
  line `regulate the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the cutting, sawing, conversion and removal of trees and timber, and the collection,`
  line `manufacture and removal of forest-produce, from protected forests;`
  line
  line `(b) the granting of licenses to the inhabitants of towns and villages in the vicinity of protected`
  line `forests to take trees, timber or other forest-produce for their own use, and the production and return of`
  line `such licenses by such persons;`
  line
  line `(c) the granting of licenses to persons felling or removing trees or timber or other forest-produce`
  line `from such forests for the purposes of trade, and the production and return of such licenses by such`
  line persons;
  line
  line `(d) the payments, if any, to be made by the persons mentioned in clauses (b) and (c) for`
  line `permission to cut such trees, or to collect and remove such timber or other forest-produce;`
  line
  line `(e) the other payments, if any, to be made by them in respect of such trees, timber and produce,`
  line `and the places where such payment shall be made;`
  line
  line `(f) the examination of forest-produce passing out of such forests;`
  line
  line `(g) the clearing and breaking up of land for cultivation or other purposes in such forests;`
  line
  line `(h) the protection from fire of timber laying in such forests and of trees reserved under section 30;`
  line
  line `(i) the cutting of grass and pasturing of cattle in such forests;`
  line
  line `(j) hunting, shooting, fishing, poisoning water and setting traps or snares in such forests, and the`
  line `killing or catching of elephants in such forests in areas in which the Elephants Preservation Act, 1879`
  line `(6 of 1879), is not in force;`
  line
  line `(k) the protection and management of any portion of a forest closed under section 30; and`
  line
  line `(l) the exercise of rights referred to in section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (31893)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Penalties for acts in contravention of notification under section 30 or of rules under section 32.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31893&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who commits any of the following offences, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) fells, girdles, lops, taps or burns any tree reserved under section 30, or strips off the bark or`
  line `leaves from, or otherwise damages, any such tree;`
  line
  line `(b) contrary to any prohibition under section 30, quarries any stone, or burns any lime or`
  line `charcoal, or collects, subjects to any manufacturing process, or removes any forest-produce;`
  line
  line `(c) contrary to any prohibition under section 30, breaks up or clears for cultivation or any other`
  line `purpose any land in any protected forest;`
  line
  line `(d) sets fire to such forest, or kindles a fire without taking all reasonable precautions to prevent its`
  line `spreading to any tree reserved under section 30, whether standing, fallen or felled, or to any closed`
  line `portion of such forest;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) infringes any rule made under section 32;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `^2(1A) Any person who in a protected forest`
  line
  line `(a) leaves burning any fire kindled by him in the vicinity of any tree reserved under`
  line `section 30, whether standing, fallen or felled, or closed portion of any protected forest;`
  line
  line `(b) fells any tree or drags any timber so as to damage any tree reserved as aforesaid, shall be liable to penalty which may extend to five thousand rupees in addition to such compensation for damage done to the forest as determined by a Forest-officer empowered under section 68.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever fire is caused willfully or by gross negligence in a protected forest, the State`
  line `Government may, notwithstanding that any penalty has been inflicted under this section, direct that in`
  line `such forest or any portion thereof the exercise of any right of pasture or to forest-produce shall be`
  line `suspended for such period as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clauses (e), (f) and (g) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (31894)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Nothing in this Chapter to prohibit acts done in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31894&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall`
  line `be deemed to prohibit any act done with the permission in writing of the Forest-officer, or in accordance`
  line `with rules made under section 32, or, except as regards any portion of a forest closed tinder section 30, or`
  line `as regards any rights the exercise of which has been suspended under section 33, in the exercise of any`
  line `right recorded under section 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (31895)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Protection of forests for special purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31895&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Governmen]t may, by notification`
  line `in the ^2[Official Gazette], regulate or prohibit in any forest or waste-land-]-`
  line
  line `(a) the breaking up or clearing of land for cultivation;`
  line
  line `(b) the pasturing of cattle; or`
  line
  line `(c) the firing or clearing of the vegetation;`
  line
  line `when such regulation or prohibition appears necessary for any of the following purposes:--`
  line
  line `(i) for protection against storms, winds, rolling stones, floods and avalanches;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the preservation of the soil on the ridges and slopes and in the valleys of hilly tracts, the`
  line `prevention of landslips or of the formation of ravines, and torrents, or the protection of land against`
  line `erosion, or the deposit thereon of sand, stones or gravel;`
  line
  line `(iii) for the maintenance of a water-supply in springs, rivers and tanks;`
  line
  line `(iv) for the protection of roads, bridges, railways and other lines of communication;`
  line
  line `(v) for the preservation of the public health.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^3[State Government] may, for any such purpose, construct at us own expense, in or upon any`
  line `forest or waste-land, such work as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) No notification shall be made under sub-section (1) nor shall any work be begun under subsection (2), until after the issue of a notice to the owner of such forest or land calling on him to show`
  line `cause, within a reasonable period to be specified in such notice, why such notification should not be made`
  line `or work constructed, as the case may be, and until his objections, if any, and any evidence he may`
  line `produce in support of the same, have been heard by an officer duly appointed in that behalf and have been`
  line `considered by the ^3[State Government].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 35 of the said Act,--`
  line
  line `(1) in sub-section (3), after the words "until after the issue" the words "by an officer authorised`
  line `by the State Government in that behalf" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(2) After sub-section (3), the following sub-section shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(4) A notice to show cause why a notification under sub-section (1) should not be made, may`
  line `require that for any period not exceeding six months, or till the date of the making of a notification,`
  line `whichever is earlier, the owner or such forest and all persons who are entitled or permitted to do`
  line `therein any or all of the things, specified in clause (i) or sub-section (1), whether by reasons of any`
  line `right, title or interest or under any licence or contract or otherwise, shall not, after the date of the`
  line `notice and for the period or until the date aforesaid, as the case may be, do any or all the things`
  line `specified in clause (i) of sub-section (1), to extent specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(5) A notice issued under sub-section (3) shall be served on the owner of such forest in the`
  line `manner provided in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the service of summons and`
  line `shall also be published in the manner prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person contravening any requisition made under sub-section (4) in a notice to show cause`
  line `why a notification under sub-section (1) should not be made shall, on conviction, be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or with both."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act XXIV of 1955, s. 4].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 35 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (4); for the words "six months" the words "one year" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (5), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(5-A) Where a notice issued under sub-section (3) has been served on the owner of a forest in`
  line `accordance with subsection (5), any person acquiring thereafter the right of ownership of that forest`
  line `shall be bound by the notice as if it had been served on him as an owner and he shall accordingly`
  line `comply with the notice, requisition and notification, if any, issued under this section.";`
  line
  line `(iii) after sub-section (6), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(7) Any person contravening any of the provisions of a notification issued under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall, on conviction, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine, or with both."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 9].`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (31896)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to assume management of forests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31896&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of neglect of, or willful disobedience to,`
  line `any regulation or prohibition under section 35, or if the purposes of any work to be constructed under that`
  line `section so require, the^1[State Government] may, after notice in writing to the owner of such forest or land`
  line `and after considering his objections, if any, place the same under the control of a Forest-officer, and may`
  line `declare that all or any of the provisions of this Act relating to reserved forests shall apply to such forest or`
  line land.
  line
  line `(2) The net profits, if any, arising from the management of such forest or land shall be paid to the said`
  line owner.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 36-A, 36-B, and 36-C in Act XVI of 1927.--After section 36 of the said Act,`
  line `the following new sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"36-A. Manner of serving notice and order under section 36.--The notice referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36 and the order, if any, made placing a forest under the control of a Forest`
  line `officer shall be served on the owner of such forest in the manner provided in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (V of 1908), for the service of summons.`
  line
  line `36-B. Period of control.--(1) The period of such control of any forest shall be for ten years from`
  line `the date of the order aforesaid ; but such period may thereafter by extended for successive periods of`
  line `not more than years each:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such control shall not in the aggregate exceed 30 years from the date`
  line `of the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The forest officer, under whose control the forest is placed, shall, not later than six months`
  line `before the expiry of any period referred to in sub-section (1) make a report regarding such control and`
  line `shall state therein whether in his opinion, any period of control should be extended.`
  line
  line `decide whether to extend any period of control or whether to terminate it in the manner provided in`
  line `the next succeeding section.`
  line
  line `(4) No period of control shall be extended unless the owner has been given reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against such extension.`
  line
  line `36-C. Termination of control.--(1) If the State Government decides to terminate any period of`
  line `control of any forest, if shall, by order published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner as`
  line `may be prescribed by rules, so declare ; and thereupon possession of the forest shall be given to the`
  line `owner, or if the owner be dead, to any person entitled to such possession, together with any sum of`
  line `money which may be standing to the credit of such owner;`
  line
  line `(2) All acts done or purported to be done by the Forest-officer in respect of any forest placed`
  line `under his control, during the period of such control or of any extension thereof, shall be binding on`
  line `the owner of such forest or any person to whom possession of the forest has been delivered under`
  line `this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXIV of 1955, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (31897)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Expropriation of forests in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31897&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case under this Chapter in which the`
  line `^1[State Government] considers that, in lieu of placing the forest or land under the control of a Forestofficer, the same should be acquired for public purposes, the ^1[State Government] may proceed to acquire`
  line `it in the manner provided by the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  line
  line `(2) The owner of any forest or land comprised in any notification under section 35 may, at any time`
  line `not less than three or more than twelve years from the date thereof, require that such forest or land shall`
  line `be acquired for public purposes, and the ^1[State Government] shall acquire such forest or land`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (31898)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Protection of forests at request of owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31898&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of any land or, if there be more than`
  line `one owner thereof, the owners of shares therein amounting in the aggregate to at least two-thirds thereof`
  line `may, with a view to the formation or conservation of forests thereon, represent in writing to the Collector`
  line `their desire--`
  line
  line `(a) that such land be managed on their behalf by the Forest-officer as a reserved or a protected`
  line `forest on such terms as may be mutually agreed upon; or`
  line
  line `(b) that all or any of the provisions of this Act be applied to such land.`
  line
  line `(2) In either case, the^1[State Government] may, by notification in the^2[Official Gazette], apply to such`
  line `land such provisions of this Act as it thinks suitable to the circumstances thereof and as may be desired by`
  line `the applicants.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38-A of Act XVI of 1927--In section 38-A of the principal Act:`
  line
  line `(1) for clause (b), the following shall be substituted:`
  line
  line `"(b) 'Forest' means a tract of land covered with trees, shrubs, bushes or woody vegetation`
  line `whether of natural growth or planted by human agency, and existing or being maintained with or`
  line `without human effort, or such tract of land on which such growth is likely to have an effect on the`
  line `supply of timber, fuel, forest produce, or grazing facilities, or on climate, streamflow, protection of`
  line `land from erosion or other such matters, and shall include--`
  line
  line `(i) land covered with stumps of trees of a forest`
  line
  line `(ii) land which is part of a forest or lies within it or was part of a forest or was lying within a`
  line `forest on the first day of July, 1952;`
  line
  line `(iii) such pasture land waterlogged or cultivable or non-cultivable land, lying within, or`
  line `adjacent to, a forest, as may be declared to be a forest by the State Government."`
  line
  line `(2) after clause (b), the following shall be added as new clause (c) and (d):`
  line
  line `"(c) 'Forest land' means a land covered by a forest or intended to be utilized as a forest; and`
  line
  line `(d) 'Prescribed' means prescribed by rules made under this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38-F of Act XVI of 1927--In section 38-F of the principal Act, between the`
  line `figure and letter "38-C", and word "related" the words, figure and letters "or 38-H" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 58-G of Act XVI of 1927-- In Section 28- G of the principal Act, te word`
  line `"and" occurring between the comma and the figure and letter "38-D" shall be deleted and thereafter`
  line `between the figure and letter "38-A" and the word "shall", the word, figure and letter "and 38- H" shall be`
  line inserted.
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Addition of new section 38-H to 38-M in Act XVI of 1927--After Section 38-G of the principal Act,`
  line `the following shall be added as new Sections 38-H to 38-M:`
  line
  line `"38-H. Power to take over management--(1) Whenever it appears to the State Government that`
  line `the taking over of the management of any particular forest, or forest land, is necessary or expedient in`
  line `the public interest or in order to secure the proper management thereof, particularly with a view to`
  line `ensure its planned development as a forest, it may by notification in the Official Gazette do so for all`
  line `or any of the said purposes for such period not exceeding fifteen years, as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) No notification under sub-section (1) shall be issued until-`
  line
  line `(a) after the issue of a notice by the Forest Officer to the claimant or the owner or tenureholder of the forest or forest forest land, as the case may be, affording him reasonable opportunity`
  line `to show cause, within a period of not less than fourteen days from the date of service of the notice`
  line `on him to be specified in such notice, why management of the forest or forest land specified`
  line `therein be not taken over; and`
  line
  line `(b) objection, if any, have been heard and disposed of by the Forest Officer in the manner`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The notice referred to in sub-section (2) shall be served upon the person concerned in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of Section 38-D.`
  line
  line `38.I. Consequences of Notification under Section 38-H.-- The State Government shall, in respect of`
  line `a forest, or forest land for which notification under Section 38-H has been issued--`
  line
  line `(i) place the forest, or forest-land, as the case may be with effect from the date of the notification,`
  line `in the charge of a Forest Officer, for carrying out the purposes mentioned in the notification, and`
  line `thereupon the provisions of Section 5 shall mutatis mutandis apply to such a forest or forest land, as`
  line `the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(ii) be liable and pay to the claimant or the owner or the tenure-holder of the forest, or forest land,`
  line `as the case may be, the balance of the income, if any, accruing to it therefrom, for the period`
  line `commencing from the date of notification till the date it is released under Section 38-L after`
  line `deducting therefrom such percentage of it, not exceeding twenty, as may be prescribed, for cost of`
  line `management and the amount, if any spent by the State Government on its development.`
  line
  line `38-J. Payment in respect of forest already in possession of the State Government-- In the case of`
  line `forest, possession whereof was taken over by the State Government prior to the commencement of the`
  line `Indian Forest (U.P. Amendment) Act, 1960, and the management whereof, is takenover in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of Section 38-H, the State Government shall, in the absence of a contract between the State Government and the person concerned to the contrary, be liable to pay, for the period`
  line `commencing from the date of possession till the issue of the notification under the said section the`
  line `balance of income accruing therefrom in accordance with the provisions of Section 38-I (ii) as if the`
  line `provisions of the aforesaid Act has been in force at all material dates and the management of such`
  line `forest had been assumed on the date of taking over possession thereof; anything contained in any`
  line `other law, custom, usage for the time being in force or contract to the contrary notwithstanding.`
  line
  line `38-K. Permission to cultivate areas lying within a forest or forest land taken over under this`
  line `Act-- (1) The State Government may, where it is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public`
  line `interest on the application of the person whose forest or forest land, as the case may be, has been`
  line `taken over under Section 38-H, allow him to cultivate such part of it, not being in excess of one fifth`
  line `of the total area of such forest or forest land, as the case may be, and such period, not being beyond`
  line `the period of its management, as may be satisfied in the order granting the permission.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) shall be submitted to the Forest Officer-incharge of the`
  line `forest or the forest land, as the case may be, who shall forward the same, with his recommendations`
  line `thereon, to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the State Government on the application under sub-section (2) shall be final`
  line `and be not questioned in any Court of law.`
  line
  line `38-L. Release of a forest or forest land from management--The State Government may, at any`
  line `time by notification in the Official Gazette, release from its management any forest or forest land, as`
  line `the case may be, takenover under Section 38-H and thereupon the forest or the forest land, as the case`
  line `may be, shall ceases to be under the management of the State Government, and the liability of the`
  line `State Government in respect of the forest or the forest land, as the case may be, shall cease with effect`
  line `from the date of release in the notification.`
  line
  line `38-M. Powers to make rules--(1) The State Government may after previous publication in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2)In Particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may-`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the items for which and the manner in which, the cost of management shall`
  line `be calculated;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the procedure for the hearing and disposal of objections under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the mode of management or development of the forest or the forest land taken`
  line `over under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribe the form of application under Section 38-K and the particulars that must be`
  line `given therein; and`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe any other matters which are to be, and may be, prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this Act shall, soon as may be after they are made, be laid before each`
  line `House of the Legislature while it is in session, for a total period of fourteen days extending in its one`
  line `session or more than one successive sessions and shall, unless some later date is appointed, take effect`
  line `from the date of their publication in the official Gazette, subject to such modifications or annulments`
  line `as the two Houses of the Legislature may agree to make; so however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done thereunder."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Insertion of a new Chapter V-A in Act XVI of 1927-- After Chapter V of the Indian Forest Act, 1927`
  line `the following shall be added as a new chapter V-A:`
  line
  line `"CHAPTER V-A`
  line
  line `OF THE CONTROL OVER FORESTS OF CLAIMANTS`
  line
  line `38-A. Definition-- In this Chapter unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context:`
  line
  line `(a) "Claimant" as respects any land means a person claiming to be entitled to the land or any`
  line `interest therein acquired, owned, settled or possessed or purported to have been acquired, owned, settled or possessed whether under, through or by any lease or licence executed prior to the`
  line `commencement of the U.P. Zamindari Abolition and Land Reforms Act, 1950, or under and in`
  line `accordance with any provision of any enactment, including`
  line
  line `(b) "Forest" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any land covered by trees and shrubs, and`
  line
  line `(ii) pasture lands.`
  line
  line `38-B. Power to regulate or prohibit breaking or clearing, etc.--(1) The State Government may by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette regulate or prohibit in any forest (situate in or upon any land of a`
  line `claimant) --`
  line
  line `(a) the breaking up or clearing of the land for cultivation or any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) the firing or clearing of the vegetation;`
  line
  line `(c) the girdling or trapping of burning of any tree or the stripping off the bark`
  line `from any tree;`
  line
  line `(d) the lopping and pollarding of trees:`
  line
  line `(e) the cutting, sawing conversion or the removal of trees-where such regulation`
  line `or prohibition appears necessary--`
  line
  line `(i) for the conversation of trees and forests; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for the improvement of grazing; or`
  line
  line `(iii) for the maintenance, increase and distribution of supply of fodder, timber or fuel, or`
  line
  line `(iv) for the protection of land against erosion; or`
  line
  line `(v) for subserving the interests of the general public.`
  line
  line `(2) No notification shall be made under sub-section (1) until after the issue of a notice to the claimant`
  line `of the land calling on him to show cause within a reasonable period, not less than fourteen days and not`
  line `exceeding thirty days, to be specified in such notice, why such notification should not be made, and until`
  line `objections, if any, and any evidence he may produce in support of the same, have been heard by an officer`
  line `not below the rank of an Assistant Collector of the first class appointed in that behalf and considered by`
  line `the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be lawful for the State Government to make the notification under sub-section (1) either in`
  line `respect of any particular forest or generally in respect of all forest situate in an area.`
  line
  line `38-C. Prohibition or regulation in emergent cases-- Where it is proposed to issue a notification in`
  line `respect of any forest or generally all the forests in any area under Section 38-B and the State Government`
  line `is satisfied that immediate action is necessary to prevent the doing of all or any of the acts mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a) to (e) of sub-section (1) of the said section, it may by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `prohibit the doing except as and in the manner specified, of such act in respect of that forest or, as the`
  line `case may be, generally all forests situate in any area as may be specified and, thereupon, no person shall,`
  line `notwithstanding any claim, right, agreement, custom, usage or law to the contrary, do any of the said acts`
  line `in such forest or forests until expiry of six months from the date of the notification and until the objection,`
  line `if any, filed in pursuance of the notice under sub-section (2), of Section 33-B, has been heard and`
  line `considered by the State Government.`
  line
  line `38-D. Service of notice-- The notice under sub-section (2) of Section 38-D shall-`
  line
  line `(a) In case of a notification affecting an individual person (Not being a corporation, firm or`
  line `body of persons) be served on that person--`
  line
  line `(i) personally by delivering or tendering to his the notice, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(iii) where the person cannot be found, by leaving an authentic copy of the notice with`
  line `some adult male member or by affixing such copy in some conspicuous part of the`
  line `premises in which he is known to have last resided or carried on business or`
  line `personally worked for gain, and`
  line
  line `(b) In the case of a notification of a general nature in relation to all forests in an area, be served`
  line `by publication in the Official Gazette and it shall not be necessary, unless the State`
  line `Government so directs, to serve the notice individually on the claimants.`
  line
  line `38-E. Application of Section 36 of Act XVI of 1927-- The provisions of Section 36 shall mutatis`
  line `mutandis apply to any regulation or prohibition notified under Section 38-B or 38-C.`
  line
  line `38-F. Penalties-- Any person who--`
  line
  line `(i) fell, girdles, lops, taps, pollards or burns any tree or strips off the bark or otherwise`
  line `damages any tree, or breaks up or clears for cultivation or any other purpose, any land in the forest`
  line `to which the notification under Section 38-B or 38-C relates, or`
  line
  line `(ii) sets fire to such forest, or kindles a fire without taking all reasonable precautions to`
  line `prevent its spreading, or`
  line
  line `(iii) permits cattle to damage any such tree, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months or with fine or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `38-G. Savings-- The powers conferred by Sections 38-B, 38-C, and 38-D shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of any other powers conferred on any authority by or under any other provision of this`
  line `Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act V of 1956, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 38-D of Act XVI of 1927.-- In Section 38-D of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh (hereinafter called the principal Act), for the word "and" and`
  line `the comma preceding it in sub-clause (iii) of clause (a) semi-colon shall be substituted and thereafter the`
  line `following new clause (aa) shall be inserted:`
  line
  line `"(aa) In case of a notification affecting a corporation , firm or body of persons, be served on the`
  line `manager, principal officer or agent thereof in the manner provided in clause (a); and".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XI of 1964, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38-F of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 38-F of the Principal Act, for clause (i) of`
  line `following shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `"(i) breaks up or clears any land for cultivation or any other purpose, fires or clears any`
  line `vegetation, girdles, taps, burns, lops, pollards, fells, cuts, saws, converts or removes any tree, or strips`
  line `off the bark from any tree, in any forest in respect of which a notification under section 33-8 of 38-C`
  line `or 38-H has been issued, or does any of the aforesaid acts in contravention of the provisions contained`
  line `in sub-section (4) of section 38-H, or".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XI of 1964, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38-H of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 38-H of the principal Act, after subsection (3) the following shall be added as sub-section (4) thereof:`
  line
  line `"(4) No person shall, after the service of the notice referred to in sub-section (2), do or permit or`
  line `cause to be done, save with the permission of the Forest Officer, any of the following acts on or in`
  line `respect of such forest or forest land, namely--`
  line
  line `(a) the breaking up or clearing of the land for cultivation or any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) the firing or clearing of the vegetation;`
  line
  line `(c) the girdling or tapping or burning of any tree or the stripping off of the bark from any tree;`
  line
  line `(d) the lopping or pollarding of trees;`
  line
  line `(e) the felling, cutting, sawing, conversion or removal of trees;`
  line
  line until--
  line
  line `(i) where objections under clause (a) of sub-section (2) have been filed, the disposal thereof`
  line `under clause (b) of that sub-section and thereafter, unless the objections have been allowed, for a`
  line `further period of six months or the publication of the notification under sub-section (1),`
  line `whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(ii) where no objections under clause (a) of sub-section (2) have been filed, the publication of`
  line `the notification under sub-section (1) or the expiry of six months from the date of service of the`
  line `notice, whichever is earlier."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XI of 1964, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
