obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (31899)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to impose duty on timber and other forest-produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31899&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government]`
  line `may levy a duty in such manner, at such places and at such rates as it may declare by notification in the`
  line `^2[Official Gazette] on all timber or other forest-produce--`
  line
  line `(a) which is produced in ^3[the territories to which this Act extends], and in respect of which the`
  line `^4[Government] has any right;`
  line
  line `(b) Which is brought from any place outside ^3[the territories to which this Act extends]:`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) In every case in which such duty is directed to be levied ad valorem, the ^1[Central Government]`
  line `may fix by like notification the value on which such duty shall be assessed.`
  line
  line `(3) All duties on timber or other forest-produce which, at the time when this Act comes into force in`
  line `any territory, are levied therein under the authority of the ^6[State Government], shall be deemed to be and`
  line `to have been duly levied under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^7[(4) Notwithstanding anything in this section, the ^6[State Government] may, until provision to the`
  line `contrary is made by ^8[Parliament], continue to levy any duty which it was lawfully levying before the`
  line commencement^9
  line `of ^10[the Constitution], under this section as then in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section authorises the levy of any duty which as between timber or`
  line `other forest-produce of the ^11[State] and similar produce of the locality outside the ^11[State] discriminates`
  line `in favour of the former, or which, in the case of timber or other forest-produce of localities outside the`
  line `^11[State], discriminates between timber or other forest-produce of one locality and similar timber or other`
  line `forest-produce of another locality.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "Local Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for "Part A States and Part C States".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  line
  line `5. The Proviso rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Central Legislature".`
  line
  line `9. That is, 26th January, 1950.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for the "Part III of the Government of India Act, 1935".`
  line
  line `11. Subs. ibid., for "Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (31900)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Limit not to apply to purchase-money or royalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31900&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall be deemed to`
  line `limit the amount, if any, chargeable as purchase-money or royalty on any timber or other forest-produce,`
  line `although the same is levied on such timber or produce while in transit, in the same manner as duty is`
  line levied.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (31901)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to make rules to regulate transit of forest-produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31901&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The control of all rivers and`
  line `their banks as regards the floating of timber, as well as the control of all timber and other forest-produce`
  line `in transit by land or water, is vested in the ^1[State Government], and it may make rules to regulate the`
  line `transit of all timber and other forest-produce.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the routes by which alone timber or other forest-produce may be imported, exported`
  line `or moved into, from or within ^2[the State];`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit the import or export or moving of such timber or other produce without a pass from`
  line `an officer duly authorised to issue the same, or otherwise than in accordance with the conditions of`
  line `such pass;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for the issue, production and return of such passes and for the payment of fees`
  line therefore;
  line
  line `(d) provide for the stoppage, reporting, examination and marking of timber or other forestproduce in transit, in respect of which there is reason to believe that any money is payable to`
  line `the^3[Government] on account of the price thereof, or on account of any duty, fee, royalty or charge`
  line `due thereon, or, to which it is desirable for the purposes of this Act to affix a mark;`
  line
  line `(e) provide for the establishment and regulation of depots to which such timber or other produce`
  line `shall be taken by those in charge of it for examination, or for the payment of such money, or in order`
  line `that such marks may be affixed to it, and the conditions under which such timber or other produce`
  line `shall be brought to, stored at and removed from such depots;`
  line
  line `(f) prohibit the closing up or obstructing of the channel or banks of any river used for the transit`
  line `of timber or other forest-produce, and the throwing of grass, brushwood, branches or leaves into any`
  line `such river or any act which may cause such river to be closed or obstructed;`
  line
  line `(g) provide for the prevention or removal of any obstruction of the channel or banks of any such`
  line `river, and for recovering the cost of such prevention or removal from the person whose acts or`
  line `negligence necessitated the same;`
  line
  line `(h) prohibit absolutely or subject to conditions, within specified local limits, the establishment of`
  line `saw-pits, the converting, cutting, burning, concealing or making of timber, the altering or effacing of`
  line `any marks on the same, or the possession or carrying of marking hammers or other implements used`
  line `for marking timber;`
  line
  line `(i) regulate the use of property marks for timber, and the registration of such marks; prescribe the`
  line `time for which such registration shall hold good; limit the number of such marks that may be`
  line `registered by any one person, and provide for the levy of fees for such registration.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may direct that any rule made under this section shall not apply to any`
  line `specified class of timber or other forest-produce or to any specified local area.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 41.--In section 41 of the principal Act, after sub-section (2) the following`
  line `new sub-sections shall be added, namely--`
  line
  line `"(2-A) The State Government may by notification in the Gazette delegate, either unconditionally`
  line `or subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, to any Forest Officer, not below`
  line `the rank of Conservator, the power to prescribe fees under clause (c) of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2-B) Notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of any court, any rule purporting to have`
  line `been made by a Conservator before the commencement of the Indian Forest (Uttar Pradesh`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1965, prescribing fees to be paid in respect of passes specified in clause (b) of subsection (2) shall be deemed to have been made under a power delegated under sub-section (2-A) as if`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2-A) were always in force and the Conservator were duly authorised`
  line `thereunder, and shall be deemed to be and always to have been valid, and shall continue in force until`
  line `altered, repealed or amended by the State Government or a duly authorised Conservator, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to authorise the prosecution or`
  line `punishment of any person under section 42 for any act done before the commencement of the said`
  line `Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 13]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 41 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 41 of the Indian Forest act, 1927 (XVI of`
  line `1927) in this application to the state of Maharashtra, in sub-section (2), after clause (h), the following new`
  line `clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(hh) regulate by grant of licences, within the forest limits or such distance therefrom not exceeding`
  line `eight kilometres as may be determined, the converting or cutting of timber in a saw mill, and`
  line `prescribe fees and conditions, subject to which such licences may be granted;`
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XV of 1965, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 41 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 41 of the Indian Forest act, 1927, in its`
  line `application to the State of Maharashtra,--`
  line
  line `(a) after sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be inserted; and shall be deemed to have`
  line `been inserted, with effect from the 12th day of September,1960, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, the State`
  line `Government may make rules to regulate by grant of licences, within the forest limits or such`
  line `distance therefrom not exceeding eighty kilometres as may be determined, the converting or`
  line `cutting of timer in a saw mill and prescribe fees and conditions, subject to which such licence`
  line `may be granted, and the manner in which, and the authority to whom, an appeal against the order`
  line `of refusal, suspension or revocation of a licence may filed.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), clause (hh) shall be deleted, and shall be deemed to have been deleted, with`
  line `effect from the 10th day of February, 1965.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XXIII of 1984, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "British India".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown"`
obj_root_law_sections_41_a:
  sectionId (31902)
  sectionNo 41A
  orderNo 42
  title `Powers of Central Government as to movements of timber across customs frontiers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31902&sectionno=41A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[41A. Powers of Central Government as to movements of timber across customs frontiers.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything in section 41, the Central Government may make rules to prescribe the route by`
  line `which alone timber or other forest-produce may be imported, exported or moved into or from^2`
  line [the
  line `territories to which this Act extends] across any customs frontier as defined by the Central Government,`
  line `and any rules made under section 41 shall have effect subject to the rules made under this section. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. (No. 3) 1956, for "Part A States and Part C States".`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (31903)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for breach of rules made under section 41.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31903&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] may by such`
  line `such rules prescribe as penalties for the contravention thereof imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to six months, or fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or both.`
  line
  line `(2) Such rules may provide that penalties which are double of those mentioned in sub-section (1) may`
  line `be inflicted in cases where the offence is committed after sunset and before sunrise, or after preparation`
  line `for resistance to lawful authority, or where the offender has been previously convicted of a like offence.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 42 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the words "two thousand rupees" the words "five thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 4].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 42.- In sub-section (1), for the words "six months" and "five hundred rupees", substitute the words "two years" and "twenty-five thousand rupees" respectively.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020.]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42--In section 42 of the principal Act, for sub-section (1), the following subsection shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) The State Government may by such rules prescribe as penalties for the contravention thereof`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees or both."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 5]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42.--In section 42 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), or the words "six`
  line `month, or fine which may extend to five hundred rupees" the words two years, or fine which may extend`
  line `to five thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 5]`
  line
  line Maharashtra--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42 of Act XVI.--In section 42 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the`
  line `words "six months or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees," the words "one year or with`
  line `fine which may extend to two thousand rupees," shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (31904)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Governments and Forest-officers not liable for damage to forest-produce at depot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31904&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The^1[Government] shall not be responsible for any loss or damage which may occur in respect of any`
  line `timber or other forest-produce while at a depot established under a rule made under section 41, or while`
  line `detained elsewhere, for the purposes of this Act; and no Forest-officer shall be responsible for any such`
  line `loss or damage, unless he causes such loss or damage negligently, maliciously or fraudulently.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (31905)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `All persons bound to aid in case of accident at depot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31905&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `In case of any accident or emergency`
  line `involving danger to any property at any such depot, every person employed at such depot, whether by the`
  line `^1[Government] or by any private person, shall render assistance to any Forest-officer or Police-officer`
  line `demanding his aid in averting such danger or securing such property from damage or loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (31906)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Certain kinds of timber to be deemed property of Government until title thereto proved, and may be collected accordingly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31906&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) All timber found adrift, beached, stranded or sunk;`
  line
  line `all wood or timber bearing marks which have not been registered in accordance with the rules made`
  line `under section 41, or on which the marks have been obliterated, altered or defaced by fire or otherwise;`
  line and
  line
  line `in such areas as the ^1[State Government] directs, all unmarked wood and timber;`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be the property of Government, unless and untill any person establishes his right and`
  line `title thereto, as provided in this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Such timber may be collected by any forest-officer or other person entitled to collect the same by`
  line `virtue of any rule made under s ion 51, and may be brought to any depot which the Forest-officer may`
  line `notify as a depot for the reception of drift timber.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[State Government] may, by notification in the ^2[Official Gazette], exempt any class of`
  line `timber from the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs.,ibid., for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (31907)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Notice to claimants of drift-timber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31907&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Public notice shall from time to time be given by the`
  line `Forest-officer of timber collected under section 45. Such notice shall contain a description of the timber,`
  line `and shall require any person claiming the same to present to such officer, within a period not less than`
  line `two months from the date of such notice, a written statement of such claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (31908)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure on claim preferred to such timber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31908&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any such statement is presented as`
  line `aforesaid, the Forest-officer may, after making such inquiry as he thinks fit, either reject the claim after`
  line `recording his reasons for so doing, or deliver the timber to the claimant.`
  line
  line `(2) If such timber is claimed by more than one person, the Forest-officer may either deliver the same`
  line `to any of such persons whom he deems entitled thereto, or may refer the claimants to the Civil Courts,`
  line `and, retain the timber pending the receipt of an order from any such Court for its disposal.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person whose claim has been rejected under this section may, within three months from the`
  line `date of such rejection, institute a suit to recover possession of the timber claimed by him; but no person`
  line `shall recover any compensation or costs against the ^1[Government], or against any Forest-officer, on`
  line `account of such rejection, or the detention or removal of any timber, or the delivery thereof to any other`
  line `person under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) No such timber shall be subject to process of any Civil, Criminal or Revenue Court until it has`
  line `been delivered, or a suit has been brought, as provided in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (31909)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 49
  title `Disposal of unclaimed timber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31909&sectionno=48&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `If no such statement is presented as aforesaid, or if the claimant`
  line `omits to prefer his claim in the manner and within the period fixed by the notice issued under section 46,`
  line `or on such claim having been so preferred by him and having been rejected, omits to institute a suit to`
  line `recover possession of such timber within the further period fixed by section 47, the ownership of such`
  line `timber shall vest in the ^1[Government], or, when such timber has been delivered to another person under`
  line `section 47, in such other person free from all encumbrances not created by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (31910)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 50
  title `Government and its officers not liable for damage to such timber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31910&sectionno=49&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Government] shall`
  line `not be responsible for any loss or damage which may occur in respect of any timber collected under`
  line `section 45, and no Forest-officer shall be responsible for any such loss or damage, unless he causes such`
  line `loss or damage negligently, maliciously or fraudulently.`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (31911)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 51
  title `Payments to be made by claimant before timber is delivered to him.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31911&sectionno=50&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be`
  line `entitled to recover possession of any timber collected or delivered as aforesaid until he has paid to the`
  line `Forest-officer or other person entitled to receive if such sum on account thereof as may be due under any`
  line `rule made under section 51.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (31912)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make rules and prescribe penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31912&sectionno=51&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government ^1[may, bynotification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, make rules] to regulate the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salving, collection and disposal of all timber mentioned in section 45;`
  line
  line `(b) the use and registration of boats used in salving and collecting timber;`
  line
  line `(c) the amounts to be paid for salving, collecting, moving, storing or disposing of such timber;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) the use and registration of hammers and other instruments to be used for marking such timber.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
  line
  line `(2) The ^3[State Government] may prescribe, as penalties for the contravention of any rules made`
  line `under this section, imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or fine which may extend to`
  line `five hundred rupees, or both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 51.--In sub-section (2), for the words "six months, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees", substitute the words "two years, or with fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 51A. --After section 51 of the principal Act the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `51A.--Power to regulate manufacture and preparation of articles based on forest produce.--(1)`
  line `the State Government may make rules,--(a) to provide for the establishment, and regulation by licence,`
  line `permit or otherwise (and the payment of fees therefor), of saw mills and other units including factories`
  line `engaged in the manufacture of preparation of the following articles: --`
  line
  line `(i) Katha (Catechu) or Kuth out of Khair wood;`
  line
  line `(ii) plywood, veneer and wood-panel products;`
  line
  line `(iii) preparation of matchboxes and match splints;`
  line
  line `(iv) boxes including packing cases made out of wood;`
  line
  line `(v) such other articles based on forest produce as the State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, from time to time, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide for the regulation by licence, permit or otherwise, of procurement of raw materials`
  line `for the preparation of the article mentioned in clause (a), the payment and deposit of fees therefor and`
  line `for due compliance of the conditions thereof, the forfeiture of the fee so deposited or any part thereof`
  line `for contravention of any such condition, and the adjudication of such forfeiture by such authority as`
  line `the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may prescribe, as penalties for the contravention of any rules made under`
  line `this section, imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees or both.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 10 of 1984, s. 4].`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "may make rules".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (31913)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 53
  title `Seizure of property liable to confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31913&sectionno=52&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) When there is reason to believe that a forestoffence has been committed in respect of any forest-produce, such produce, together with all tools, boats,`
  line `carts or cattle used in committing any such offence, maybe seized by any Forest-officer or Police-officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer seizing any property under this section shall place on such property a mark`
  line `indicating that the same has been so seized, and shall, as soon as may be, make a report of such seizure to`
  line `the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure has been made:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when the forest-produce with respect to which such offence is believed to have been`
  line `committed is the property of Government, and the offender is unknown, it shall be sufficient if the officer`
  line `makes, as soon as may be, a report of the circumstances to his official superior.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 52 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) sub-section (1A) shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(b) in the marginal note, the words "and forfeiture" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 5].`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52.--In sub-section (1) of section 52 of the principal Act, the words "carts or`
  line `cattle", the words and mark "carts, vehicles or cattle" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 10 of 1984, s. 5].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 52.--Substitute section 52 with the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `"52. Seizure of property liable to confiscation and procedure thereof.-- (1) When there is reason to believe that a forest offence has been committed in respect of any reserved forest, protected forest, village forest or forest produce, the forest produce, together with all tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article used in committing any such offence, may be seized by a Forest Officer or Police Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer seizing any property under this section shall place on such property a mark indicating that the same has been so seized and shall, as soon as may be, make a report of such seizure before an officer not below the rank of the Divisional Forest Officer (hereinafter referred to as the authorised officer):`
  line
  line `Provided that when the forest produce with respect to which such offence is believed to have been committed is the property of the Government and the offender is unknown, it shall be sufficient if the officer makes, as soon as may be, a report of the circumstances to his official superior.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to sub-section (5), where the authorised officer upon receipt of report about seizure, is satisfied that a forest offence has been committed in respect thereof, he may, by order in writing and for reasons to be recorded, confiscate forest produce so seized together with all tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article used in committing such offence and a copy of the order of confiscation shall be forwarded without any undue delay to the person from`
  line `Trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871), shall apply in respect of the charges to be levied for the upkeep and fee of whom the property is seized and to the Conservator of Forest Circle in which the forest produce, tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article as the case may be, has been seized.`
  line
  line `(4) No order confiscating any property shall be made under sub-section (3) unless the authorised officer,--`
  line
  line `(a) sends an intimation in writing about initiation of proceedings for confiscation of the property to the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure has been made;`
  line
  line `(b) issues a notice in writing to the person from whom the property is seized and to any other person who may, in the opinion of the authorised officer to have some interest in such property;`
  line
  line `(c) affords an opportunity to the persons referred to in clause (b) of making a representation within such reasonable time as may be specified in the notice against the proposed confiscation; and`
  line
  line `(d) gives to the officer effecting the seizure and the person or persons to whom notice has been issued under clause (b), a hearing on date to be fixed for such purpose.`
  line
  line `(5) No order of confiscation under sub-section (3) of any tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article (other than timber or forest produce seized) shall be made if any person referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (4) proves to the satisfaction of authorised officer that any such tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article were used without his knowledge or connivance or, as the case may be, without the knowledge or connivance of his servant or agent and that all reasonable and necessary precautions had been taken against the use of objects aforesaid for commission of forest offence.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the cattle are involved in the commission of a forest offence, the same after seizure by any officer, shall be entrusted to any responsible person under a proper receipt on an undertaking to produce the same when required in case there is no cattle pound within a radius of five kilometres from the place of such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything contained in section 57, in case of unclaimed cattle a Forest Officer not below the rank of Range Officer, after giving sufficient publicity in the vicinity of the place of offence for the owner to come forward to claim the cattle within seven days from the date when such publicity has been given, may dispose them of by public auction.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of the Cattle Trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871), shall apply in respect of the chargesto`
  line `be levied for the upkeep and fee of the cattle.`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 52A to 52D.-- After section 52, insert the following sections, namely:--`
  line
  line `52A. Revision before Court of Sessions against order of confiscation.-- (1) Any party aggrieved by an order of confiscation under section 52 may within thirty days of the order or if facts of the confiscation have not been communicated to him, within thirty days of knowledge of such order submit a petition for revision to the Court of Sessions Division whereof the headquarters of Authorised Officer are situated.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--In computing the period of thirty days under this sub-section, the time required for obtaining certified copy of the order of Authorised Officer shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this sub-section a party shall be deemed to have knowledge of the order of confiscation under section 52 on publication of such order in two daily newspapers having circulation in the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court of Sessions may confirm, reverse or modify any final order of confiscation passed by the Authorised Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of the order passed in revision shall be sent to the Authorised Officer for compliance or passing such further order or for taking such further orders or for taking such further action as may be directed by such Court.`
  line
  line `(4) For entertaining, hearing and deciding a revision under this section, the Court of Sessions shall, as far as may be, exercise the same powers and follow the same procedure as it exercises and follows while entertaining, hearing and deciding a revision under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) the order of Court of Sessions passed under this section shall be final and shall not be called in question before any Court.`
  line
  line `52B. Bar to jurisdiction of Courts etc. under certain circumstances.--(1) On receipt of report under`
  line `sub-section (4) of Section 52 about intimation of proceedings for confiscation of property by the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure of property which is subject matter of confiscation, has been made, no Court, Tribunal or Authority other than Authorised Officer and Court of Sessions referred to in sections 52 and 52A shall have jurisdiction to make orders with regard to possession, delivery, disposal or distribution of the property in regard to which proceedings for confiscation are initiated under section 52, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where under any law for the time being in force, two or more Courts have jurisdiction to try the forest offences, then receipt of intimation under sub-section (4) of section 52 by one of the Courts shall operate as bar to exercise jurisdiction on all such other Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the power saved under section 61 of the Act.`
  line
  line `52C. Power of search and seizure.--(1) Any Forest Officer or Police Officer may, if he has reason to believe that a vehicle has been or is being used for the transport of forest produce in respect of which there is reason to believe that a forest offence has been or is being committed, require the driver or other person in charge of such vehicle to stop the vehicle and cause it to remain stationary as long as may reasonably be necessary to examine the contents in the vehicle and inspect all records relating to the goods carried which are in the possession of such driver or other person in charge of the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) Any forest officer not below the rank of Range officer, having reasonable grounds to believe that forest produce is, in contravention of the provisions of this Act, in the possession of a person in any place, may enter such place with the object of carrying out a search for the forest produce and its confiscation:`
  line
  line `Provided that such search shall not be conducted otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `52D. Penalty for forcibly opposing seizure.--Whosoever opposes the seizure of any forest-produce, tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article liable to be seized under this Act, or forcibly receives the same after seizure, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to twenty five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section.--After Section 52 of the Principal Act, the following new`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `52A. Confiscation of saw mill etc.--(1) Where a Saw Mill is established, maintained or operated`
  line `without a licence or without renewal of a licence the authorised officer may order confiscation of the`
  line `stock of wood together with whole or portion of the plants, machinery, implements, tools, and equipments`
  line `of the Saw Mill.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the authorised officer seizes under sub-section (1) of Secion 52 any forest produce or where`
  line `any such property is produced before the authorised officer after seizure by any Forest Officer and he is`
  line `satisfied that a forest offence has been committed in respect of such property, such authorised officer`
  line `may, whether or not a prosecution instituted for the commission of such forest offence, order confiscation`
  line `of the property so seized together with all tools, equipments, ropes, chains, boats, carts, vehicles and`
  line `cattle used in committing such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) No order confiscating any property shall be made under Sub-Section (1) or Sub-section (2) unless`
  line `the person from whom the property is seized and in case the owner of such property is known, such`
  line `person is given--`
  line
  line `(a) a notice in writing informing him the grounds on which it is proposed to confiscate such`
  line property;
  line
  line `(b) an opportunity of making representation in writing within such reasonable time as may be`
  line `specified in the notice against the grounds for confiscation; and`
  line
  line `(c) a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) Any Forest Officer not below the rank of Conservator of Forsts empowered by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification, may within 30 days from the date of order of confiscation by`
  line `the authorised officer under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) either suo-moto or on application, call for`
  line `and examine the records of that order and may make such inquiry or cause such inquiry to be made and`
  line `pass orders as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `Provided that no order prejudical to any person shall be passed without giving him an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) Any persons aggrieved by an order passed under sub-sections (l), (2) or (4) may within thirty days`
  line `from the date of communication to him of such order, appeal to the District Court having jurisdiction over`
  line `the area in which the property has been seized and the District Court shall after giving an opportunity to`
  line `the parties to be heard; pass such order as it may think fit and the order of the District Court so passed`
  line `shall be final. Where an order of confiscation of any property passed under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) has become final in respect of the whole or any portion of such`
  line `property; such property or the portion there of; as the case may be shall vest in the State Government free`
  line `from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section authorised officer means an officer not below the rank`
  line `of Assistant Conservator of Forest authorised by the State Government by notification.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Tripura Act 8 of 1987, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52--In section 52 of the principal Act, ---`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words`
  line `"vehicles or cattle" the words "vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains or other articles" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for sub-section (2), the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"(2) Any Forest Officer or Police Officer may, if he has reason to believe that a boat or vehicle has`
  line `been, or is being, used for the transport of any forest produce in respect of which a forest offence has`
  line `been, or is being, committed, require the driver or other person in charge of such boat or vehicle to stop it,`
  line `and he may detain such boat or vehicle for such reasonable time as is necessary to examine the contents in`
  line `such boat or vehicle and to inspect the records relating to the goods transported so as to ascertain the`
  line `claims, if any, of the driver or other person in charge of such boat or vehicle regarding the ownership and`
  line `legal origin of the forest produce in question.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer seizing any property under this section shall place on such property a mark`
  line `indicating that the same has been so seized and shall, as soon as may be, make a report of such seizure to`
  line `the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure has been made, and if`
  line `the seizure is in respect of forest produce which is the property of the State Government, shall also make`
  line `a report to the authorised officer."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Amendment of Sections 52, 53 and 55 of Act XVI of 1927-- In sub-section (1) of Section 52 and`
  line `Section 53 and 55 of the principal Act, for the word Carts wherever occurring the word "Vehicles"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXI of 1960, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 52-A, 52-B, 52-C and 52-D--`
  line
  line `52-A. procedure on seizure--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law`
  line `for the time being in force where a forest offence is believed to have been committed in respect of any`
  line `forest produce, which is the property of the State Government, the officer seizing the property under subsection (1) of section 52 shall, without unreasonable delay, produce it together with all the tools, boats,`
  line `vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains and other articles used in committing the offence, before an officer, not`
  line `below the rank of a Divisional Forest Officer, authorised by the State Government in this behalf, who`
  line `may, for reasons to be recorded, make an order in writing with regard to custody, possession, delivery,`
  line `disposal or distribution of such property, and in case of tools, boats, vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains and`
  line `other articles, may also confiscate them.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised officer shall, without any undue delay, forward a copy of the order made under`
  line `sub-section (1) to his official superior.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the authorised officer passing an order under subsection (1) is of the opinion that the`
  line `property is subject to speedy and natural decay he may order the property or any part thereof to be sold by`
  line `public auction and may deal with the proceeds as he would have dealt with such property if it had not`
  line `been sold and shall report about every such sale to his official superior.`
  line
  line `(4) No order under sub-section (1) shall be made without giving notice, in writing, to the person from`
  line `whom the property is seized, and to any other person who may appear to the authorised officer to have`
  line `some interest in such property:`
  line
  line `Provided that in an order confiscating a vehicle, when the offender is not traceable, a notice in writing`
  line `to the registered owner thereof and considering his objections if any will suffice.`
  line
  line `(5) No order of confiscation of any tool, boat, vehicle, cattle, rope, chain or other article shall be`
  line `made if any person referred to in sub-section (4) proves to the satisfaction of the authorised officer that`
  line `any such tool, boat, vehicle, cattle, rope, chain or other article was used without his knowledge or connivance or without the knowledge or connivance of his servant or agent, as the case may be, and that`
  line `all reasonable recautions had been taken against use of the objects aforesaid for the commission of the`
  line `forest offence.`
  line
  line `52-B. Appeal--Any person aggrieved by an order of confiscation may, with in thirty days of the date`
  line `of Communication to him of such order, prefer an appeal to the State Government and the State`
  line `Government shall, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the appellant and the authorised officer`
  line `pass such order as it may think fit confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against and the`
  line `order of the State Government shall be final.`
  line
  line `52-C. Order of confiscation not to prevent any other punishment--No order of`
  line `confiscation under section 52-A or 52-B shall prevent the indication of any punishment to which the`
  line `person affected thereby may be liable under this Act.`
  line
  line `52-D. Bar of jurisdiction in certain cases--Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `this Act or in the code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `whenever any forest produce belonging to the State Government together with any tool, boat, vehicle,`
  line `cattle, rope, chain or other article is seized under sub-section (1) of section 52, the authorised officer`
  line `under section 52-A or the State Government under section 52-B shall have jurisdiction, to the exclusion`
  line `of every other officer, court, Tribunal or authority, to make orders with regard to the custody, possession,`
  line `delivery, disposal or distribution of the property."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 7.]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52.--In section 52 of the Principal Act--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words "carts or cattle " the words "vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains or`
  line `other articles " shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for sub-section (2), the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Any Forest Officer or Police Officer may, if he has reason to believe that a boat or vehicle`
  line `has been, or is being, used for the transport of any forest produce in respect of which a forest offence`
  line `has been, or is being, committed, require the driver or other person in charge of such boat or vehicle`
  line `to stop it, and he may detain such boat or vehicle for such reasonable time as is necessary to examine`
  line `the contents in such boat or vehicle and to inspect the records relating to the goods transported so as`
  line `to ascertain the claims, if any, of the driver or other person in charge of such boat or vehicle regarding`
  line `the ownership and legal origin of the forest produce in question.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer seizing any property under this section shall place on such property a mark`
  line `indicating that the same has been so seized and shall, as soon as may be, make a report of such`
  line `seizure to the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure has been made, and if the seizure is in respect of forest produce which is the property of the State`
  line `Government, shall also make a report to the authorised officer. ".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 52-A, 52-B, 52-C and 52-D.--After section 52 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `52-A. Procedure on seizure.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, where a forest offence is believed to have been committed in respect`
  line `of any forest produce, which is the property of the State Government, the officer seizing the property`
  line `under sub-section (1) of Section 52 shall, without unreasonable delay, produce it together with all the`
  line `tools, boats, vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains and other articles used in committing the offence before an`
  line `officer, not below the rank of a Divisional Forest Officer, authorised by the State Government in this`
  line `behalf, who may, for reasons to be recorded, make an order in writing with regard to custody,`
  line `possession, delivery, disposal or distribution of such property, and in case of tools, boats, vehicles,`
  line `cattle, ropes, chains and other articles, may also confiscate them.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorised officer shall, without any undue delay, forward a copy of the order made under`
  line `sub-section (1) to his official superior.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the authorised officer passing an order under sub-section (1) is of the opinion that the`
  line `property is subject to speedy and natural decay he may order the property or any part thereof to be`
  line `sold by public auction and may deal with the proceeds as he would have dealt with such property if it`
  line `had not been sold and shall report about every sale to his official superior.`
  line
  line `(4) No order under sub-section (1) shall be made without giving notice, in writing, to the person`
  line `from whom the property is seized, and to any other person who may appear to the authorised officer`
  line `to have some interest in such property :`
  line
  line `Provided that in an order confiscating a vehicle, when the offender is not traceable, a notice in`
  line `writing to the registered owner thereof and considering his objections if any will suffice.`
  line
  line `(5) No order of confiscation of any tool, boat, vehicle, cattle, ropes, chain or other article shall be`
  line `made if any person referred to in sub-section (4) proves to the satisfaction of the authorised officer`
  line `that any such tool, boat, vehicle, cattle, rope, chain or other article was used without his knowledge or`
  line `connivance or without the knowledge or connivance of his servant or agent, as the case may be, and`
  line `that all reasonable precautions had been taken against use of the objects aforesaid for the commission`
  line `of the forest offence.`
  line
  line `52-B. Appeal.--Any person aggrieved by an order of confiscation may, within thirty days of the`
  line `date of communication to him of such order, prefer an appeal to the Conservator of Forests of the`
  line `circle who shall, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the appellant and the authorised officer,`
  line `pass such order as it may think fit confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against and`
  line `the order of the Conservator of Forests of the circle shall be final.`
  line
  line `52-C. Order of confiscation not to prevent any other punishment.--No order of confiscation`
  line `under Section 52-A or 52-B shall prevent the infliction of any punishment to which the person`
  line `affected thereby may be liable under this Act.`
  line
  line `52-D. Bar of Jurisdiction in certain cases.--Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in this Act or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `whenever any forest produce belonging to the State Government together with any tool, boat, vehicle,`
  line `cattle, rope, chain or other article is seized under sub-section (1) of Section 52, the authorised officer`
  line `under Section 52-A or the State Government under Section 52-B shall have jurisdiction, to the`
  line `exclusion of every other officer, court, Tribunal or authority, to make orders with regard to the`
  line `custody, possession, delivery, disposal or distribution of the property. ".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 52 of the principal act,--`
  line
  line `(a) after sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be inserted namely :--`
  line
  line `"(1A) Any Forest Officer or Police Officer may, if he has reason to believe that a vehicle has`
  line `been or is being used for the transport of forest produce in respect of which there is reason to believe`
  line `a forest offence has been or is being committed, require the driver or other person in charge of such`
  line `vehicle to stop the vehicle and cause it to remain stationary as long as may be reasonably be`
  line `necessary to examine the contents in the vehicle and inspect all records relating to the goods carried`
  line `which are in the possession of such driver or other person in charge of the vehicle";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2) after the words "on such property, " the words and brackets "or the`
  line `receptacle or vehicle (if any) in which it is contained," shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after the proviso, the following shall be added, namely :--`
  line
  line `"Provided further that, where the offence on account of which the seizure has been made in`
  line `respect of timber, sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or such other forest produce as may be notified by`
  line `the State Government, from time to time (hereinafter referred to as the notified forest produce") and`
  line `which is the property of the State Government, such officer shall make a report of such seizure also to`
  line `the concerned authorised officer under section 61A.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "property of Government" and`
  line `"property of the State Government include the property belonging to the Forest Development`
  line `Corporation of Maharashtra, Limited";"`
  line
  line `(c) in the marginal note, for the word "confiscation" the words "confiscation and forfeiture" shall`
  line `be substituted."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 7.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 52, 53 and 55 Act XVI of 1927.--In sections 52, 53 and 55 of the Indian Forest`
  line `Act, 1927 (XVI of 1927), for the word "carts", wherever it occurs, the word "vehicles" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XXV of 1953, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (31914)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to release property seized under section 52.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31914&sectionno=53&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Any Forest-officer of a rank not inferior`
  line `to that of a Ranger who, or whose subordinate, has seized any tools, boats, carts or cattle under section`
  line `52, may release the same on the execution by the owner thereof a bond for the production of the property`
  line `so released, if and when so required, before the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence on`
  line `account of which the seizure has been made.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 53.-For section 53, substitute the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `53 Power to release property seized under section 52.- Any forest officer of a rank not inferior to that of a Range Officer, who, or whose subordinate, has seized any tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article used in committing any forest offence, including the forest produce, under section 52, may release the same on the execution by the owner thereof, of a security in a form of a bank guarantee, of an amount not less than the value of such property, as estimated by such officer, for the production of the property so released when so required by the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence or by the authorised officer empowered under sub-section (2) of section 52, on account of which the seizure has been made:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any forest produce is seized at a remote location from where it is not practicable to transport it immediately, the officer who, or whose subordinate has effected such seizure under section 52, may entrust the same (Supardnama) to any responsible person on the execution of a bond thereof, by such person, for the production of the property so entrusted if and when required by the Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the offence or before the authorised officer empowered under sub-section (2) of section 52, on account of which the seizure has been made.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 52 and 53, (16 of 1927).--In section 52 and 53 of the said Act, for the word`
  line `"carts" wherever it occurs the word "vehicle" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 11 of 1954, s. 3]`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 53.--In section 53 of the principal Act, for the words "carts or cattle", the`
  line `words and mark "carts, vehicles or cattle" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Tripura Act 10 of 1984, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 53--In section 53 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "vehicles or cattle" the words "vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains or other articles"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(ii) after the words "the seizure has been made" the words "except in respect of cases falling`
  line `under section 52-A for which the procedure laid down in that section shall be followed" shall be`
  line inserted.]
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (31915)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 55
  title `Procedure thereupon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31915&sectionno=54&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Upon the receipt of any such report, the Magistrate shall, with all`
  line `convenient is despatch, take such measures as may be necessary for the arrest and trial of the offender and`
  line `the disposal of the property according to law.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 54.--For section 54, substitute the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `"54 Receipt of report of seizure by Magistrate and procedure thereupon.-- Upon the receipt of any report under sub-section (4) of section 52, the Magistrate shall, with all convenient dispatch, take such measures as may be necessary for the arrest and trial of the offender and the disposal of the property according to law:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing any order for disposal of property the Magistrate shall satisfy himself that no intimation under sub-section (4) of section 52 has been received by his court or by any other court having jurisdiction to try the offence on account of which the seizure of property has been made.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 54 of Act XVI of 1927.--For section 54 of the principal act, the following`
  line `section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"54. Procedure on receipt by Magistrate of report of seizure.-- Upon the receipt of any report`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 52, the Magistrate shall, with all convenient dispatch, take such`
  line `measures as may be necessary for the arrest and trial of the offender and the disposal of the property`
  line `according to law:`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (31916)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 56
  title `Forest-produce, tools, etc., when liable to confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs., ibid., for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31916&sectionno=55&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) All timber or forest-produce`
  line `which is not the property of ^1[Government] and in respect of which a forest-offence has been committed,`
  line `and all tools, boats, carts and cattle used in committing any forest-offence, shall be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `(2) Such confiscation may be in addition to any other punishment prescribed for such offence.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 55 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words shall be liable by order of the convicting court to forfeiture the words shall be liable to confiscation shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), for the word forfeiture the word confiscation shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) in the marginal note, for the word forfeiture the word confiscation shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 6].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 55.- For sub-section (1), substitute the following sub-section:--`
  line
  line `(1) All timber or forest produce which in either case is not the property of the Government and in respect of which a forest offence has been committed, and all tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article, in each case used in committing any forest offence shall, subject to the provisions of section 52, 52A and 52B, be liable to confiscation upon conviction of the offender for such offence.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55--In section 55 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1) for the words`
  line `"vehicle and cattle used in committing any forest offence" the words "vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains and`
  line `other articles used in committing such forest office" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 9].`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55.--In section 55 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1) for the words`
  line `"Carts and cattle used in committing any forest offence" the words "vehicles, cattle, ropes, chains and`
  line `other articles used in committing forest offence" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand 10 of 2002, s. 9].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 55 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words "shall be liable to confiscation," the words, figures and letter`
  line `"shall, subject to section 61G, be liable by order of the convicting court to forfeiture.", shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), for the word "confiscation" the word "forfeiture" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) in the marginal note, for the word "confiscation" the word "forefeiture" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 10].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 52,53 and 55 Act XVI of 1927.--In sections 52, 53 and 55 of the Indian Forest`
  line `Act, 1927 (XVI of 1927), for the word "carts", wherever it occurs, the word "vehicles" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XXV of 1953, s. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (31917)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 57
  title `Disposal, on conclusion of trial for forest-offence, of produce in respect of which it was committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31917&sectionno=56&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `When the trial of any forest-offence is concluded, any forest-produce in respect of which`
  line `such offence has been committed shall, if it is the property of ^1[Government] or has been confiscated, be`
  line `taken charge of by a Forest-officer, and, in any other case, may be disposed of in such manner as the`
  line `Court may direct.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 56 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 56 of the principal Act, for the word "forfeited" the word "confiscated" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 7].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 56.--For the words "When the trial of", substitute the words, figures and letter, "Without prejudice to the provisions of section 52C, when the trial of".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 56 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 56 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the word "confiscated" the word "forefeited" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "in any other case, may be disposed of” the words, figures and letters "in any`
  line `other may, subject to section 61G, be disposed of” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 11].`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (31918)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 58
  title `Procedure when offender not known, or cannot be found.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31918&sectionno=57&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `When the offender is not known or`
  line `cannot be found, the Magistrate may, if he finds that an offence has been committed, order the property in`
  line `respect of which the offence has been committed to be confiscated and taken charge of by the Forestofficer or to be made over to the person whom the Magistrate deems to be entitled to the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made until the expiration of one month from the date of seizing`
  line `such property, or without hearing the person, if any, claiming any right thereto, and the evidence, if any,`
  line `which he may produce in support of his claim.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 57 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 57 of theprincipal Act, for the word forfeited the word confiscated shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 8].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 57.--For section 57, substitute the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `"57. Procedure when the offender is not known or cannot be found.-- When the offender is not known or cannot be found the Magistrate may, if he finds that an offence has been committed, but subject to section 52B, order the property in respect of which offence has been committed, to be confiscated or forfeited together with all tools, arms, boats, carts, equipment, ropes, chains, machines, vehicles, cattle or any other article used in committing the offence, and taken charge of by the Forest officer, or to be made over to the person whom the Magistrate deems to be entitled to the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that, no such order shall be made until the expiration of one month from the date of seizing such property or without hearing the person, if any, claiming any right thereto, and the evidence, if any, which he may produce in support of his claim."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 57--In section 57 of the principal Act, for the words "The Magistrate may"`
  line `the words "the Magistrate, subject to section 52-D may." shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 10]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 57.--In section 57 of the principal Act, for the words "The Magistrate may"`
  line `the words "The Magistrate, subject to section 52-D, may" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 10]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 57 of Act XVI of 1927.-- In section 57 of the principal Act, for the portion`
  line `beginning with the words "the Magistrate may" and ending with the words to be confiscated" the`
  line `following shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"the Magistrate may, if he finds that an offence has been committed, but subject to section 61G,`
  line `order the property in respect of which the offence has been committed, to be forfeited together with`
  line `tools, boats, vehicles or cattle and other articles used in committing the offence.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra act VII of 1985, s. 12]`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (31919)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Procedure as to perishable property seized under section 52.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31919&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, direct the sale of any property seized under section 52`
  line `and subject to speedy and natural decay, and may deal with the proceeds as he would have dealt with such`
  line `property if it had not been sold.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 58.--For section 58, substitute the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `58. Procedure as to perishable property seized under section 52. -- The Authorised Officer under sub-section (2) of section 52, or the Magistrate may, notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, direct the sale of any property seized under section 52 and subject to speedy and natural decay, and may deal with the proceeds as he would have dealt had it not been sold.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 58--Ins section 58 of the principal Act, for the words "The Magistrate may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained," the words "Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore`
  line `contained, but subject to sub-section (3) of section 52-A, the Magistrate may," shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 11]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 58.--In section 58 of the principal Act for the words "The Magistrate may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything herein before contained," the words, "Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore`
  line `contained, but subject to sub-section (3) of section 52-A, the magistrate may" Shall be substituted.`
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 11]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 58 of Act XVI of 1927.--For section 58 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be substituted namely:--`
  line
  line `"58. Procedure as to perishable seized under section 52.--The Forest-officer who made the`
  line `seizure under section 52 may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law, sell`
  line `any property seized under section 52 and subject to speedy and natural decay, and may deal with the`
  line `proceeds as he would have dealt with such property if it had not been sold and shall report about`
  line `every such sale to his official superior.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 13]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (31920)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Appeal from orders under section .55, section 56 or section 57.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31920&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The officer who made the`
  line `seizure under section 52, or any of his official superiors, or any person claiming to be interested in the`
  line `property so seized, may, within one month from the date of any order passed under section 55, section 56`
  line `or section 57, appeal therefrom to the Court to which orders made by such Magistrate are ordinarily`
  line `appealable, and the order passed on such appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (31921)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 61
  title `Property when to vest in Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31921&sectionno=60&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `60. Property when to vest in ^1[Government].-- When an order for the confiscation of any property`
  line `has been passed under section 55 or section 57, as the case may be, and the period limited by section 59`
  line `for an appeal from such order has elapsed, and no such appeal has been preferred, or when on such an`
  line `appeal being preferred, the Appellate Court confirms such order in respect of the whole or a portion of`
  line `such property, such property or such portion thereof, as the case may be, shall vest in the ^1[Government]`
  line `free from all incumbrances.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 60 of the principal Act, for the word "forfeiture" the word "confiscation" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 9].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 60.--Renumbered as sub-section (2) thereof, and, before sub-section (2) as so renumbered, insert the following sub-section, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) Property ordered to be confiscated by an authorised officer under section 52, subject to the result of revision before Court of Sessions under section 52A shall upon conclusion of proceedings in revision, vest in the Government free from all encumbrances:`
  line
  line `Provided that if no revision is preferred under section 52A, such vesting shall take effect on expiry of period specified for the submitting petition for revision under section 52A.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60--Section 60 of the principal Act shall be renumbered as sub-section (1)`
  line `thereof and 'after sub-section (1) as so renumbered the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) When an order for confiscation has been passed under section 52-A and the period of`
  line `limitation for an appeal or revision has elapsed and no appeal or revision has been preferred or when`
  line `in appeal or revision the order for confiscation for whole or a portion of the property has been`
  line `confirmed, the property or such portion, as the case may be, shall vest in the State Government free`
  line `from all encumbrances."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 12]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60 of Act XVI of 1927.---In section 60 of the principal act, for the words`
  line `"confiscation" the word "forfeiture" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra act VII of 1985, s. 14]`
  line
  line Uttarkhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60.--- Section 60 of the principal Act shall be renumbered as sub-section (1)`
  line `thereof and after sub-section (1) as so renumbered the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) When an order for confiscation has been passed under Section 52-A and the period of`
  line `limitation for an appeal or revision has elapsed and no appeal or revision has been preferred or when`
  line `an appeal or revision the order for confiscation for whole or a portion of the property has been`
  line `confirmed, the property or such portion, as the case may be, shall vest in the State Government free`
  line `from all encumbrances.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttaranchal Act 24 of 2014, s. 12]`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (31922)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 62
  title `Saving of power to release property seized.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.,ibid.,for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31922&sectionno=61&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Nothing hereinbefore contained shall be deemed`
  line `to prevent any officer empowered in this behalf by the ^1[State Government] from directing at any time the`
  line `immediate release of any property seized under section 52.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61A of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 61A of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (3), the following sub-section shall be substituted:--`
  line
  line `"(3) Where any timber, sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or any other notified forest-produce, which is the property of the State Government, is seized under sub-section (1) of section 52, or any such forest-produce is produced before any authorised officer under sub-section (1) and he is satisfied that a forest-offence has been committed in respect of such forest-produce, notwithstanding whether or not a prosecution is instituted for the commission of such offence, such authorised officer shall order the forest-produce so seized to be taken charge of by a Forest-officer, and may order confiscation of all tools, boats, vehicles and cattles used in committing such offence.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4),--`
  line
  line `(i) for clause (a), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(a) where the authorised officer, after passing an order of confiscation under sub-section (3), is of the opinion that it is expedient in the public interest so to do, he may order sale of all confiscated tools, boats, vehicles and cattles.";`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (b),--`
  line
  line `(1) the words property or the shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(2) for the word auction the word sale shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 10].`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61B of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 61B of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), the words "any timber, sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or any other notified forest-produce," shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(3) When the offender or the owner of any tool, boat, vehicle or cattle seized under, sub-section (1) of section 52 is not known or cannot to found, and the authorised officer is satisfied that the same has been used in committing a forest-offence in respect of timber, fire-wood, sandalwood, charcoal or any other notified forest-produce which is the property of the State Government, notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions, the authorised officer may pass order in accordance with the provisions contained in section 61A:`
  line
  line `Provided that, no such order shall be made until the expiration of a period of thirty days form the date of seizing such property or without hearing the person claiming any right thereto.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 11].`
  line
  line `Substitution of section 61F of Act 16 of 1927.--For section 61F of the principal Act, the following section shall substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `61F. Property etc. confiscated when to vest in Government.--When an order for confiscation of any property has been passed under section 61A or section 61C, and the period of limitation provided by section 61D for filing an appeal against such order has elapsed, and no such appeal has been preferred or when on such an appeal being preferred, the Appellate Court confirms such order in respect, of the whole or a portion of such property, such property of such portion thereof, or if it has been sold under section 58 or under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 61A, the sale proceeds thereof, as the case may be, shall vest in the State Government free from all encumbrances.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 12].`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61G of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 61G of the principal Act, for the word "offence" the words "forest-offence in respect of such property" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 13].`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 61-B and 61-C--After section 61-A of the principal Act, the following`
  line `sections shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"61-B. Summary eviction of unauthorised occupants--(1) If a Forest Officer, not below the`
  line `rank of a Divisional Forest officer, is of the opinion that any person is in unauthorised occupation of`
  line `any land in areas constituted as a reserved or protected forest under section 20 or section 29 as the`
  line `cases may be, and that he should be evicted, the Forest Officer shall issue a notice in writing calling`
  line `upon the person concerned to show cause, on or before such date as is specified in the notice, why an`
  line `order of eviction should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) If after considering the cause, if any, shown in pursuance of a notice under this section, the`
  line `Forest Officer is satisfied that the said land is in unauthorised occupation he may make an order of`
  line `eviction for reasons to be recorded therein, directing that the said land shall be vacated by such date, as may be specified in the order, by the person concerned, which shall not be less than ten days from`
  line `the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person refuses or fails to comply with the order of eviction by the date specified in the`
  line `order, the Forest Officer who made the order under sub-section (2) or any other Forest Officer, duly`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf, may evict that person from and take possession of the said land and`
  line `may, for this purpose, use such force as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Forest Officer under sub-section (2) may, within`
  line `such period and in such manner as may be prescribed, appeal against such order to the Conservator of`
  line `Forests of the circle or to such officer as may be authorised by the State Government in this behalf`
  line `and the order of the Forest Officer shall, subject to the decision in such appeal, be final.`
  line
  line `61-C. Disposal of Property left on land by unauthorised occupant--(1) Where any person has`
  line `been evicted from any land under section 61-B, the Forest Officer may, after giving not less than ten`
  line `days notice to the person from whom possession of the land has been taken, remove or cause to be`
  line `removed or dispose of, by public auction, any property remaining on such land including any material`
  line `of a demolished building or standing crop.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any property is sold under sub-section (1) the sale proceeds thereof shall, after`
  line `deducting the expenses of the sale and the expenses necessary to restore the land to its original`
  line `condition, be paid to the person concerned."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 13]`
  line
  line `Addition of new section 61-A--After section 61 of the principal Act, the following new section shall be`
  line `added, namely--`
  line
  line `61-A. Summary eviction of persons convicted of certain offences.--Where a Court convicts`
  line `any person of an offencesunder clause (a), clause (b) or clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 26`
  line `of clause (c) or clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 33, it may, when passing judgment,`
  line `direct the eviction of such person from any land in respect of which the offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any court of appeal or or revision may direct any order under sub-section (1) passed by a`
  line `Court subordinate there to be stayed pending consideration by the former Court and may modify, alter`
  line `or annul such order."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 14]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 61-A and 51-B.--After section 61-A of the principal act, the following`
  line `sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"61-A. Summary eviction of unauthorised occupants.--(1) If a Forest Officer, not below the rank`
  line `of a Divisional Forest Officer, is of the opinion that any person is in unauthorised occupation of any land`
  line `in areas constituted as a reserved or protected forest under Section 20 or Section 29, as the case may be,`
  line `and that he should be evicted, the Forest Officer shall issue a notice in writing calling upon the person`
  line `concerned to show cause, on or before such date as is specified in the notice, why an order of eviction`
  line `should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) If after considering the cause, if any, shown in pursuance of a notice under this section, the Forest`
  line `Officer is satisfied that the said land is in unauthorised occupation, he may make an order of eviction for`
  line `reasons to be recorded therein, directing that the said land shall be vacated by such date, as may be specified in the order, by the person concerned, which shall not be less than ten days from the date of the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) If any person refuses or fails to comply with the order of eviction by the date specified in the`
  line `order, the Forest Officer who made the order under sub-section (2) or any other Forest Officer, duly`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf, may evict that person from and take possession of the said land and may,`
  line `for this purpose, use such force as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Forest Officer under sub-section (2) may, within such`
  line `period and in such manner as may be prescribed, appeal against such order to the Conservator of Forests`
  line `of the circle or to such officer as may be authorised by the State Government in this behalf and the order`
  line `of the Forest Officer shall, subject to the decision in such appeal, be final.`
  line
  line `61-B. Disposal of property left on land by unauthorised occupant.--(1) Where any person has`
  line `been evicted from any land under Section 61-B, the Forest Officer may, after giving not less than ten days`
  line `notice to the person from whom possession of the land has been taken remove or cause to be removed or`
  line `dispose of, by public auction, any property remaining on such land including any material of a`
  line `demolished building or standing crop.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any property is sold under sub-section (1) the sale proceeds thereof shall, after deducting`
  line `the expenses of the sale and the expenses necessary to restore the land to its original condition, be paid to`
  line `the person concerned.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 13]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 61 of the principal act, for the words and`
  line `figures "seized under section 52" the following shall be substituted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"seized under section 52 which is not the property of Government and the withdrawal of any charge`
  line `made in respect of such property.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 15]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 61A of 61G in act XVI of 1927.--After section 61 of the principal act, the`
  line `following sections shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"61A. Confiscation by Forest officer of forest produce where forest offence is believed to have`
  line `been committed.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter or`
  line `any other law, where a forest offence is believed to have been committed in respect of timber,`
  line `sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or any other notified forest produce which is the property of State`
  line `Government, the officer seizing the property under sub-section (1) of section 52 shall, without any`
  line `unreasonable delay produce it, together with all tools, boats, vehicles and cattle used in committing such`
  line `offence, before an officer authorised by the State Government in this behalf by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, not being an officer below the rank of an Assistant Conservator of Forests (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as "the authorised officer").`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may authorize one or more officers for any local area under sub-section`
  line `(1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where an authorised officer seizes under sub-section (1) of section 52 any timber, sandalwood,`
  line `firewood, charcoal or any other notified forest produce which is the property of the State Government or`
  line `any such property is produced before an authorised officer under sub-section (1) and he is satisfied that a`
  line `forest offence has been committed in respect of such property, such authorised officer may, whether or`
  line `not a prosecution is instituted for the commission of such forest offence, order confiscation of the`
  line `property so seized together with all tools, boats, vehicles and cattle used in committing such offence.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) Where the authorised officer, after passing an order of confiscation under sub-section (3), is`
  line `of the opinion that it is expedient in the public interest so to do, he may order the confiscated property or`
  line `any part thereof and the tools, boats, vehicles and cattle to be sold by public auction,`
  line
  line `(b) Where any confiscated property or the tools, boats, vehicles and cattle are sold, aforesaid, the`
  line `proceeds thereof, after deduction of the expenses of any such auction or other incidental expenses relating`
  line `thereto shall, where the order of confiscation made under this section is set aside or annulled by an order`
  line `under section 61C or 61D, be paid to the owner thereof or to the person from whom it was seized as may`
  line `be specified in such order.`
  line
  line `61B. Issue of show cause notice before confiscation under section 61A.--(1) No order confiscating`
  line `any timber, sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or any other notified forest produce, tools, boats, vehicles or`
  line `cattle shall be made under section 61A except after notice in writing to the person from whom it is seized`
  line `and considering his objections, if any :`
  line
  line `Provided that no order confiscating a motor vehicle shall be made except after giving notice in`
  line `writing to the registered owner thereof, if in the opinion of the authorised officer it is practicable to do so,`
  line `and considering his objections, if any.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), no order confiscating a tool, boat, vehicle`
  line `or cattle shall be made under section 61A if the owner of the tool, boat, vehicle or cattle proves to the`
  line `satisfaction of the authorised officer that it was used in carrying the timber, sandalwood, firewood,`
  line `charcoal or any other notified forest produce without the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself,`
  line `his agent, if any, and the person in charge of the tool, boat, vehicle or cattle and that each of them had`
  line `taken all reasonable and necessary precautions against such use.`
  line
  line `61C. Revision.--Any Forest Officer not below the rank of Conservator of Forests specially`
  line `empowered by the State Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette, may suo motu`
  line `call for and examine the record of the order of the authorised officer under section 61 A; and may make`
  line `such inquiry or cause such inquiry to be made and may pass such orders as he deems fit :`
  line
  line `Provided that no such record shall be called for after the expiry of 30 days from the date of such`
  line `order, and no order under this section shall be passed if in the meanwhile, an appeal has been filed under`
  line `section 61D against the order of the authorised officer :`
  line
  line `Provided further that no order prejudicial to a person shall be passed under this section without giving`
  line `him an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `61D. Appeal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by any order passed under section 61A or section 61C may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date of communication to him of such order, appeal to the Sessions Judge`
  line `having jurisdiction over the area in which the property and the tools, boats, vehicles and cattle to which`
  line `the order relates has been seized and the Sessions Judge shall, after giving an opportunity to the appellant`
  line `and the authorised officer or the officer specially empowered under section 61C, as the case may be, to be`
  line `heard, pass such order as he may think fit confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) An order of the Session Judge under sub-section (1) shall be final and shall not be questioned in`
  line `any Court.`
  line
  line `61E. Award of confiscation not to interfere with other punishments.--The award of any`
  line `confiscation under section 61A or section 61C or section 61D shall not prevent the infliction of any`
  line `punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
  line
  line `61F. Property etc., confiscated when to vest in Government.--When an order for confiscation of`
  line `any property or any tools, boats, vehicles or cattle is passed under section 61A or section 61C or Section`
  line `61D and such order has become final in respect of the whole or any portion of such property, or tool,`
  line `boat, vehicle or cattle, such property or portion thereof or tool, boat vehicle or cattle or if it has been sold`
  line `under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 61A, the sale proceeds thereof, as the case may be, shall vest`
  line `in the State Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `61G. Bar of jurisdiction in certain cases.--Whenever any timber, sandalwood, firewood, charcoal or`
  line `any other notified forest produce which is the property of the State Government, together with any tool,`
  line `boat, vehicle or cattle used in committing any offence is seized under sub-section (1) of section 52, the`
  line `authorised officer under section 61A or the officer specially empowered under section 61C or the Sessions Judge hearing the appeal under section 61D shall have, and notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in this Act or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, or in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, any other officer, Court, Tribunal or authority shall not have, jurisdiction to make orders`
  line `with regard to the custody, possession, delivery, disposal or distribution of such property and any tool,`
  line `boat, vehicle or cattle."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 16]`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (31923)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 63
  title `Punishment for wrongful seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31923&sectionno=62&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Any Forest-officer or Police-officer who vexatiously and`
  line `unnecessarily seizes any property on pretence of seizing property liable to confiscation under this Act`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 62 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), the words "or forfeiture" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 14].`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62 of Act XVI of 1927.--Section 62 of the principal act shall be re-numbered as`
  line `sub-section (1) thereof and,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1) as so re-numbered, for the word "confiscation" the words "confiscation or`
  line `forfeiture" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (1) as so re-numbered, the following sub-section shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Any fine so imposed, or any portion thereof, shall, if the convicting court so directs, be given`
  line `as compensation to the person aggrieved by such seizure."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 17].`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (31924)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 64
  title `Penalty for counterfeiting or defacing marks on trees and timber and for altering boundary-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31924&sectionno=63&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with intent to cause damage or injury to the public or to any person, or to cause`
  line `wrongful gain as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860),--`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly counterfeits upon any timber or standing tree a mark used by Forest-officers to`
  line `indicate that such timber or tree is the property of the ^1[Government] or of some person, or that it may`
  line `lawfully be cut or removed by some person; or`
  line
  line `(b) alters, defaces or obliterates any such mark placed on a tree or on timber by or under the`
  line `authority of a Forest-officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) alters, moves, destroys or defaces any boundary-mark of any forest or waste-land to which the`
  line `provisions of this Act are applied,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 63.--For the words, "or with fine", substitute the words "or with fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (31925)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31925&sectionno=64&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Forest-officer or Police-officer may, without orders`
  line `from a Magistrate and without a warrant, arrest any person against whom a reasonable suspicion exists of`
  line `his having been concerned in any forest-offence punishable with imprisonment for one month or upwards.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer making an arrest under this section shall, without unnecessary delay and subject to`
  line `the provisions of this Act as to release on bond, take or send the person arrested before the Magistrate`
  line `having jurisdiction in the case, or to the officer in charge of the nearest police-station.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise such arrest for any act which is an offence`
  line `under Chapter IV unless such act has been prohibited under clause (c) of section 30.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 64A.--After section 64, insert the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `64A. Offences non-bailable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act other than those compoundable under section 68 shall be non-bailable.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central`
  line `Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 64 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section on 64 of the principal act, in subsection (1), for the words "Any Forest Officer or Police Officer", the words "Any Forest Officer, Police`
  line `Officer or Revenue Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 961, s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (31926)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title `Power to release on a bond a person arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31926&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Any Forest-officer of a rank not interior to that`
  line `of a Ranger, who, or whose subordinate, has arrested any person under the provisions of section 64, may`
  line `release such person on his executing a bond to appear, if and when so required, before the Magistrate`
  line `having jurisdiction in the case, or before the officer in charge of the nearest police station.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 65A of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 65A of the principal Act, in clause (b), for the words, figures, brackets and letters Section 26, clauses (a), (b), (f), (g), (h) and (i) of sub-section (1), the words, figures, brackets and letters Section 26, clauses (a), (b), (d), (f), (g), (h) and (i) of`
  line `sub-section (1) and sub-section (4) shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 15].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 65A and 65B.--After section 65, insert the following sections, namely:--`
  line
  line `65A. Requisition for police assistance.-Any forest officer may requisition the services of any police officer to assist him for all or any of the purposes specified in sections 52, 63 and 64 and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line
  line `65B. Police officers bound to seek technical clearance from Authorized Officer.-Any police officer seizing any property under the provisions of this Act or rules framed there under shall be bound to seek technical clearance of the authorized officer to lodge a complaint to the magistrate under section 52 of this Act.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 65-A--After section 65 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `65-A. Certain offences to be non-bailable--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act`
  line `or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 any offence punishable under section 26, or section`
  line `33 or section 42 or section 63 shall be non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(2) No person accused of any offence as aforesaid shall, if in custody, be released on application`
  line `for released on bail or on his own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the prosecution has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such release,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) Where the prosecution opposes the application as aforesaid the court is satisfied that there`
  line `are reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 14]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 65-A.--After section 65 of the principal Act, the following sections shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"65-A. Certain offences to be non-bailable.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act or in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, any offence punishable under Section 26 or Section`
  line `33 or Section 42 or Section 63 shall be non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(2) No person accused of any offence as aforesaid shall, if in custody, be released on bail or on`
  line `his own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the prosecution has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such release,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) where the prosecution opposes the application as aforesaid, the court is satisfied that there`
  line `are reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offences.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttaranchal Act 10 of 2002, s. 14`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 65 of Act XVI of 1927.-- In section 65 of the principal Act, for the words "a`
  line `Ranger" the words "a Ranger, any Police Officer" of a rank not inferior to that of Sub-Inspector or any`
  line `Revenue Officer of a rank not inferior to that of Mahalkari or Tahsildar" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 11`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 65 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 65 of the principal act, for the words`
  line `"may release such person" the words, figures and letter "may, subject to and without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 65A, release such person" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 18`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 65A in Act XVI of 1927.--After section 65 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"65A. Certain offences to be non-bailable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or`
  line `in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973,--`
  line
  line `(a) The offences under sections or clauses of sections mentioned in clause (b) shall be nonbailable.`
  line
  line `(b) The sections and clauses of sections of this Act referred to in clause (a) are the following,`
  line `namely :-Section 26, clauses (a), (b), (f), (g), (h) and (i) of sub section (1).`
  line
  line `Section 33, clauses (a), (b), (c), (d), (f) and (h) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `Section 42.`
  line
  line `Section 63.`
  line
  line `(c) No person accused of any offence referred to in clause (b) shall, if in custody, be released`
  line `on bail or on his own bond unless,--`
  line
  line `(i) the prosecution has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release, and`
  line
  line `(ii) where the prosecution opposes the application, the Court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 2985, s. 19]`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (31927)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power to prevent commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31927&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Every Forest-officer and Police-officer shall`
  line `prevent, and may interfere for the purpose of preventing, the commission of any forest-offence.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 66A in Act 16 of 1927.--After section 66 of the principal Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `66A. Punishment for abetment--Whoever abets any forest-offence shall, if the offence abetted is committed in consequence of abetment, be punished with the same punishment as is provided for such offence,.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 16].`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 66-A--`
  line
  line `66-A. Penalty for not preventing commission of forest offence--Whoever, being a`
  line `Forest Officer or Police Officer, bound under section 66 to prevent commission of any forest offence,`
  line `intentionally or knowingly, neglects or omits to prevent or abets, the commission of such offence,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine or with`
  line `both."]`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 15]].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 66 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 66 of the principal Act, for the words`
  line `"Every Forest Officer and Police Officer" the words "Every Forest Officer, Police Officer and Revenue`
  line `Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 12].`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (31928)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 68
  title `Power to try offences summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31928&sectionno=67&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The District Magistrate or any Magistrate of the first class`
  line `specially empowered in this behalf by the ^1[State Government] may try summarily, under the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), any forest-offence punishable with imprisonment for a term not`
  line `exceeding six months, or fine not exceeding five hundred rupees, or both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 67 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 67 of the principal Act, for the words "two thousand rupees" the words "five thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 17].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 67.--For the words "not exceeding six months, or fine not exceeding five hundred rupees", substitute the words "not exceeding two years or with fine not exceeding twenty five thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `[Videthe Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 67 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 67 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words and figures "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" the words and figures "the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "not exceeding six months, or fine not exceeding five hundred rupees or both"`
  line `the words "not exceeding one year, or fine not exceeding two thousand rupees, or both, and the`
  line `provisions of sections 262 to 265 (both inclusive of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to`
  line `such trial; but, notwithstanding anything contained in the said Code, in the case of conviction for any`
  line `offence in a summary trial under this section, it shall be lawful for the Magistrate to pass sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for any term for which such offence, is punishable under this Act shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s. 20]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (31929)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to compound offences and impose penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31929&sectionno=68&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] may, by`
  line `notification in the ^2[Official Gazetted], empower a Forest officer-`
  line
  line `(a) to accept from any person against whom a reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed`
  line `any forest-offence, other than an offence specified in section 62 or section 63, a sum of money by`
  line `way of compensation for the offence which such person is suspected to have committed ^3[`
  line `; or]`
  line
  line `[^4(aa) to accept from any person a sum of money by way of penalty or compensation for violation`
  line `of sub-section (1A) of section 26 or sub-section (1A) of section 33; and]`
  line
  line `(b) when any property has been seized as liable to confiscation, to release the same on payment of`
  line `the value thereof as estimated by such officer.`
  line
  line `(2) On the payment of such sum of money, or such value, or both, as the case may be, to such officer,`
  line `the suspected person, if in custody, shall be discharged, the property, if any seized shall be released, and`
  line `no further proceedings shall be taken against such person or property.`
  line
  line `(3) A Forest-officer shall not be empowered under this section unless he is a Forest-officer of a rank`
  line `not inferior to that of a Ranger and is in receipt of a monthly salary amounting to at least one hundred`
  line `rupees, and the sum of money accepted as compensation under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall in no`
  line `case exceed the sum of fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for ", and" (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (31930)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 70
  title `Presumption that forest-produce belongs to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31930&sectionno=69&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `69. Presumption that forest-produce belongs to ^1[Government]. --When in any proceedings`
  line `taken under this Act, or in consequence of anything done under this Act, a question arises as to whether`
  line `any forest-produce is the property of the ^1[Government], such produce shall be presumed to be the`
  line `property of the ^1[Government] until the contrary is proved.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 69.--For the words, "contrary is proved", substitute the words "contrary is proved by the`
  line `accused".`
  line
  line `Section 69-A.--After section 69, insert the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `69-A. Double penalties for offences.--The penalties which are double of those mentioned under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or rules framed thereunder shall be inflicted in cases where the offence is`
  line `committed after sunset and before sunrise, or after preparation for resistance to lawful authority or where`
  line `the offender has been previously convicted of a like offence.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (31931)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 71
  title `Cattle-trespass Act, 1871, to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31931&sectionno=70&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Cattle trespassing in a reserved forest or in any portion of`
  line `a protected forest which has been lawfully closed to grazing shall be deemed to be cattle doing damage to`
  line `a public plantation within the meaning of section 11 of the Cattle-trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871), and may`
  line `be seized and impounded as such by any Forest-officer or Police-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (31932)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power to alter fines fixed under that Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31932&sectionno=71&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The^1[State Government] may, by notification in`
  line `the^2[Official Gazette] , direct that, in lieu of the fines fixed under section 12 of the Cattle-trespass Act,`
  line `1871 (1 of 1871), there shall be levied for each head of cattle impounded under section 70 of this Act`
  line `such fines as it thinks fit, but not exceeding the following, that is to say:-`
  line
  line `For each elephant.................................................... ...ten rupees.`
  line
  line `For each buffalo or camel................... ..two rupees.`
  line
  line `For each horse, mare, gelding, pony, colt, filly, mule, bull, bullock, cow, or heifer.......... one rupee.`
  line
  line `For each calf, ass, pig, ram, ewe, sheep, lamb, goat or kid.................................... ....eightannas.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 71 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 71 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "ten rupees" the words "Two hundred rupees" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "two rupees" the words "Two hundred rupees" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) for the words "one rupees" the words "Two hundred rupees" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(d) for the words "fifty nayepaise" the words "One hundred rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 19].`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 71.--For the words "ten rupees", "two rupees", "one rupee" and "eight annas", substitute the words "one thousand rupees", "two hundred and fifty rupees", "one hundred rupees" and "fifty rupees" respectively.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 71 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 71 of the principal Act, for the the words`
  line `"eight annas" the words "fifty naye paise" shall be substituted.br`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 14.]`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (31933)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 73
  title `State Government may invest Forest-officers with certain powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31933&sectionno=72&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The^1[State`
  line `Government] may invest any Forest-officer with all or any of the following powers, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(a) power to enter upon any land and to survey, demarcate and make a map of the same;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of a Civil Court to compel the attendance of witnesses and the production of`
  line `documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `(c) power to issue a search-warrant under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898); and`
  line
  line `(d) power to hold an inquiry into forest-offences, and, in the course of such inquiry, to receive`
  line `and record evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) Any evidence recorded under clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be admissible in any subsequent`
  line `trial before a Magistrate, provided that it has been taken in the presence of the accused person.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 72.--For section 72, substitute the following section, namely;`
  line
  line `72. Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may invest Forest officers with certain powers.- (1) The forest officers shall have the following powers, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) power to enter upon any land and to survey, demarcate and make a map of the same.`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of a Civil Court to compel the attendance of witnesses and the production of documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `(c) power to hold an inquiry into forest offences and in the course of such inquiry, to receive and record evidence; and`
  line
  line `(d) power to issue search warrants under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that powers under clause (b) and (c) shall not be exercised by a forest officer below the rank of a Range Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the powers under clause (d) shall not be exercised by a forest officer below the rank of a Divisional Forest Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Any evidence recorded under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be admissible in any subsequent trial before a Magistrate, if that it has been taken in the presence of the accused person.`
  line
  line `(3) Any forest officer not below the rank of a Range Officer may delegate his powers of inquiry to an officer of the rank of Forester if the offence is compoundable under section 68 of this Act.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 72.--In section 72 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), in clause (c), for the`
  line `words and figures "Code of Criminal Producer, 1898" the words and figures "the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VII of 1985, s.21]`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (31934)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 74
  title `Forest-officers deemed public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31934&sectionno=73&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `All Forest-officers shall be deemed to be public`
  line `servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (31935)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 75
  title `Indemnity for acts done in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31935&sectionno=74&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall lie against any public servant for anything`
  line `done by him in good faith under this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 74.--For section 74, substitute the following section, namely:-`
  line
  line `74. Indemnity for acts done in good faith.--(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall lie against any public servant for anything done in good faith or omitted to be done likewise, under this Act or the rules or orders made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence alleged to have been committed by a forest officer`
  line `while acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his official duty except with the previous sanction of the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of section 74--For section 74 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"74. Indemnity for acts done in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the State Government or any public servant for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or rules or orders made thereunder."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 17]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Substitution of section 74.--For section 74 of the principal act the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"74. Indemnity for acts done in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the State Government or any public servant for anything done by him under this Act`
  line `or rules or orders made thereunder.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 16]`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (31936)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 76
  title `Forest-officers not to trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31936&sectionno=75&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Except with the permission in writing of the ^51[State Government],`
  line `no Forest-officer shall, as principal or agent, trade in timber or other forest-produce, or be or become`
  line `interested in any lease or any forest or in any contractfor working any forest, whether in or outside ^53[the`
  line `territories to which this Act extends].`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for "Part A States and Part C States".`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (31937)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 77
  title `Additional powers to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31937&sectionno=76&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] may make rule--`
  line
  line `(a) to prescribe and limit the powers and duties of any Forest-officer under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to regulate the rewards to be paid to officers and informers out of the proceeds of fines and`
  line `confiscation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) for the preservation, reproduction and disposal of trees and timber belonging to Government,`
  line `but grown on lands belonging to or in the occupation of private persons; and`
  line
  line `(d) generally, to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 76A.--After section 76, insert the following section, namely:-`
  line
  line `76A. Power to regulate manufacture and preparation of articles based on forest produce.--(1) The Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may make rules,--`
  line
  line `(a) to provide for the establishment, and regulation by licence, permit or otherwise (and the payment of fees thereof), of saw mills, timber depots, firewood depots and other units including the factories or industries engaged in the consumption of forest produce or manufacture or preparation of the following articles:-`
  line
  line `(i) katha (catechu) or kutch out of khairwood;`
  line
  line `(ii) rosin, turpentine, other products out of resin, and wood oil;`
  line
  line `(iii) plywood, veneer and wood-based products;`
  line
  line `(iv) match boxes and match splints;`
  line
  line `(v) boxes including packing cases made out of wood;`
  line
  line `(vi) joinery and furniture items made out of wood;`
  line
  line `(vii) charcoal, lime stone and gypsum;`
  line
  line `(viii) such other articles based on forest produce as the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may, by notification in the Official Gazette, from time to time, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide for the regulation by licence, permit or otherwise, of procurement of raw material for the preparation of articles mentioned in clause (a), the payment and deposit of fees therefor and for due compliance of the condition thereof, the forfeiture of the fees so deposited or any part thereof for contravention of any such condition and adjudication of such forfeiture by such authority as the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may provide that, as the contravention of any rules made under this section shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to twenty five thousand rupees, or both.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (31938)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 78
  title `Penalties for breach of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31938&sectionno=77&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Any person contravening any rule under this Act, for the`
  line `contravention of which no special penalty is provided, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one month, or fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 77.-For the words "extend to one month, or fine which may extend to five hundred rupees", substitute the words "extend to two years or with fine which may extend to twenty five thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 77.--In section 77 of the principal Act, for the words "one month, or fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees", the words "one year, or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees", shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 18]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Amendment of section 77.--In section 77 of the principal Act for the words "one month, or fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees" the words "one year, or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 17]`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (31939)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 79
  title `Rules when to have force of law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31939&sectionno=78&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `All rules made by the ^1[State Government] under this Act`
  line `shall be published in the ^2[Official Gazette], and shall thereupon, so far as they are consistent with this`
  line `Act, have effect as if enacted therein.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substitution of new section for section 78.--For section 78 of the principal Act, the following shall`
  line `be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"78. Further provisions regarding rules.--(1) All rules under this Act shall be made by`
  line `notification in the Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) All rules made under this Act shall, as soon as may be after they are made, laid before`
  line `each House of the State Legislature, while it is in session, for total period of fourteen days which may`
  line `be comprised in its one session or in two or more successive sessions and shall, unless some latter`
  line `date is appointed take effect from the date of their publication in the Gazette subject to such`
  line `modifications or annulments as the two Houses of the Legislature may agree to make, so however`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done thereunder."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIII of 1965, s. 15]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 78 of Act XVI of 1927.--Section 78 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) of`
  line `that section and after the sub-section so renumbered, the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :--]`
  line
  line `"(2) All rules made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid for not less than thirty`
  line `days before each House of the State Legislature as soon as possible after they are made and shall be`
  line `subject to such modification as the State Legislature may make during the session in which they are`
  line `so laid, or the session immediately following and publish in the Official Gazette.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 15]`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (31940)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 80
  title `Persons bound to assist Forest-officers and police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31940&sectionno=79&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who exercises`
  line `any right in a reserved or protected forest, or who is permitted to take any forest-produce from, or to cut`
  line `and remove timber or to pasture cattle in, such forest, and every person who is employed by any such`
  line `person in such forest, and`
  line `every person in any village contiguous to such forest who is employed by the^1Government], or who`
  line `receives emoluments from the^1[Government] for services to be performed to the community,shall be`
  line `bound to furnish without unnecessary delay to the nearest Forest-officer or Police-officer any information`
  line `he may possess respecting the commission of, or intention to commit, any forest-offence, and shall`
  line `forthwith take steps, whether so required by any Forest-officer or Police officer or not,--`
  line
  line `(a) to extinguish any forest fire in such forest of which he has knowledge or information;`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent by any lawful means in his power any fire in the vicinity of such forest of which he`
  line `has knowledge or information from spreading to such forest,and shall assist any Forest-officer or`
  line `Police-officer demanding his aid--`
  line
  line `(c) in preventing the commission in such forest of any forest-offence; and`
  line
  line `(d) when there is reason to believe that any such offence has been committed in such forest in`
  line `discovering and arresting the offender.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, being bound so to do, without lawful excuse (the burden of proving which shall`
  line `lie upon such person) fails--`
  line
  line `(a) to furnish without unnecessary delay to the nearest Forest-officer or Police-officer any`
  line `information required by sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) to take steps as required by sub-section (1), to extinguish any forest fire in a reserved or`
  line `protected forest;`
  line
  line `(c) to prevent, as required by sub-section (1), any fire in the vicinity of such forest from spreading`
  line `to such forest; or`
  line
  line `(d) to assist any Forest-officer or Police-officer demanding his aid in preventing the commission`
  line `in such forest of any forest-offence, or, when there is reason to believe that any such offence has been`
  line `committed in such forest, in discovering and arresting the offender;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 79.-In sub-section (2), in the long line, for the words shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees substitute the words, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Section 79A to 79C.-After section 79, insert the following sections, namely:-`
  line
  line `79-A. Penalty for unauthorisedly taking possession of land constituted as reserved or protected forest.-(1) Any person who unauthorisedly takes or remains in possession of any land in areas constituted as reserved forest or protected forest under section 20 or section 29 as the case may be, may, without prejudice to any other action that may be taken against him under any other provision of this Act, be summarily ejected by order of a forest officer not below the rank of a Divisional Forest Officer and any crop which may be standing on such land or any building or other work which he may have constructed thereon, if not removed by him within such time as such forest officer may fix, shall be liable to forfeiture:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of ejectment under this sub-section shall be passed unless the person proposed to be ejected is given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause why such an order should not be passed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any property so forfeited shall be disposed of in such manner as the forest officer may direct and the cost of removal of any crop, building or other work and, of all works necessary to restore the land to its original condition shall be recoverable from such person in the manner provided in section 82.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order of the forest officer under sub-section (1) may, within sixty days from the date of such order prefer an appeal by petition in writing to the concerned Chief Conservator of Forests in person or through a duly authorized agent and such petition shall be accompanied by a certified copy of the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of the appeal and after summoning the parties and perusing the record of the proceedings, the Chief Conservator of Forests shall fix a date and convenient place for hearing the appeal and shall give notice thereof to the parties, and shall hear the appeal accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) The order passed on the appeal by the Chief Conservator of Forests shall be final.`
  line
  line `79B. Summary action by Deputy Commissioner in fire cases.- If in any case under clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) of section 79, it appears to the Deputy Commissioner of the district within which the forest concerned is situated after local enquiry made in a summary and administrative manner, either by himself, or through a Tehsildar deputed by him for the purpose, that any such person or village or other community has neglected to give such information or to render such assistance as is required thereby, he may impose a fine not exceeding one thousand rupees on, as well as direct payment of compensation for damage to Governments property by, such person, village or other community or such individual member of such village or other community as may be determined in consultation with the Divisional Forest Officer and all fines imposed under this section shall be recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `79C. Appeal against order of Deputy Commissioner.- An appeal against every order passed under section 79B may be made to the concerned Divisional Commissioner whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, Order No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 79--In section 79 of the principal Act, for the words "one month, or fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees", the words "one year, or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees", shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 19]`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (31941)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 81
  title `Management of forests the joint property of Government and other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31941&sectionno=80&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `80. Management of forests the joint property of ^2[Government] and other persons.--(1) If the`
  line `^2[Government] and any person be jointly interested in any forest or waste-land, or in the whole or any part`
  line `of the produce thereof, the ^1[State Government] may either--`
  line
  line `(a) undertake the management of such forest, waste-land or produce, accounting to such person`
  line `for his interest in the same; or`
  line
  line `(b) issue such regulations for the management of the forest, waste-land or produce by the person`
  line `so jointly interested as it deems necessary for the management thereof and the interests of all parties`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) When the`
  line `^3[State Government] undertakes under clause (a) of sub-section (1) the management of`
  line `any forest, waste-land or produce, it may, by notification in the^4[Official Gazette] , declare that any of the`
  line `provisions contained in Chapters II and IV shall apply to such forest, waste-land or produce, and`
  line `thereupon such provisions shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80-A in Act XIV of 1927--After section 80 of Indian Forest Act 1927, the`
  line `following shall be added as a new section 80-A:`
  line
  line `"80-A. The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that any of the`
  line `provisions of or under this Act, shall apply to all or any or any land on the banks of canals or the sides`
  line `of roads which are the property, of the State Government or a local authority and thereupon such`
  line `provisions shall apply accordingly."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XVIII of 1951, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80--A in Act XVI of 1927.--After section 80 of the said act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"80-A. Power of Government to apply provisions of this Act to pertain lands of Government`
  line `or local authority.--The State Government, may be notification in the Official Gazette, declare that`
  line `any of the provisions of this act shall apply to all or any lands on the banks of canals or the sides of`
  line `roads which are the property of the State Government or a local authority and thereupon such`
  line `provisions shall apply to such lands accordingly."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXIV of 1955, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (31942)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 82
  title `Failure to perform service for which a share in produce of Government forest is enjoyed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31942&sectionno=81&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `81. Failure to perform service for which a share in produce of ^2[Government] forest is`
  line `employed.--If any person be entitled to a share in the produce of any forest which is the property of`
  line `^2[Government] or over which the ^2[Government] has proprietary rights or to any part of the forestproduce of which the Government is entitled upon the condition of duly performing any service`
  line `connected with such forest, such share shall be liable to confiscation in the event of the fact being`
  line `established to the satisfaction of the^1[State Government] that such service is no longer so performed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such share be confiscated until the person entitled thereto, and the evidence, if any,`
  line `which he may produce in proof of the due performance of such service, have been heard by an officer`
  line `duly appointed in that behalf by the^1[State Government] .`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown".`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (31943)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 83
  title `Recovery of money due to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31943&sectionno=82&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `All money payable to the Government under this`
  line `Act, or under any rule made under this Act, or on account of the price of any forest-produce, or of`
  line `expenses incurred in the execution of this Act in respect of such produce, may, if not paid when due, be`
  line `recovered under the law for the time being in force as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82 of Act 16 of 1927.--In section 82 of the principal Act, the words and figures "or on account of compensation or value of property agreed to be paid under section 68" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 21 of 2015, s. 20].`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82, (16 of 1927).--For section 82 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 (16 of`
  line `1927), the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"82. All money, other than fines, payable to the State Government under this Act, or any rules made`
  line `thereunder, or on account of timber or other forest produce, or of expenses incurred in the execution of`
  line `this Act in respect of timber or other forest produce, or under any contract relating to timber and other`
  line `forest produce including any sum recoverable thereunder for the breach thereof, or in consequence of its`
  line `cancellation, or under the terms of a notice relating to the sale of timber or other forest produce by auction`
  line `or by invitation of tenders, issued by or under the authority of a Forest Officer and all compensation`
  line `awarded to the State Government under this Act, may, if not paid when due, be recovered, under the law`
  line `for the time being in force, as if it were an arrear of land-revenue."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 25 of 1952, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 82.-For section 82, substitute the following section, namely:-`
  line
  line `"82. Recovery of money due to Government.- All money payable to the Government under this Act or under any rule made under this Act, or on account of the price of timber, or other forest produce, or of expenses incurred in execution of this Act in respect of timber and other forest produce, or under any contract relating to timber and other forest produce including any sum recoverable there under for breach thereof, or in consequence of its cancellation, or under the terms of a notice relating to the sale of timber or other forest produce by auction or by invitation of tenders, issued by or under authority of a forest officer and all compensation awarded to the Government under this Act shall, if not paid when due, be recovered, under the law for the time being in force, as if it were an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Section 82-A to 82-H.-After section 82, insert the following sections, namely:-`
  line
  line `82-A. Recovery of penalties due under a bond.-When in respect of any forest lease any person binds himself by any bond or instrument to perform any duty or act, or covenants by any bond or instrument that he, or that he and his servant and agents will abstain from any act, the whole sum mentioned in such bond or instrument as the amount to be paid in case of a breach of the conditions thereof shall notwithstanding anything in section 74 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872, be recovered from him in case of such breach as if it were an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `82-B. Restoration of advantage or benefit or payment of compensation.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in the Indian Contract Act, 1872, or in any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) where any transaction or lease relating to sale of forest produce or extraction of timber from any forest is or is discovered to be void only on the ground that the transaction or lease is not in conformity with the provisions of article 299 of the Constitution of India or any order or direction issued thereunder, any person who has received any advantage or has enjoyed any benefit by virtue of such transaction or lease shall be bound to restore it or to make compensation for it, to the person or party from whom he received it;`
  line
  line `(b) the extent of any advantage or benefit or the amount of compensation payable in lieu thereof, referred to in clause (a), shall be determined in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the value of the advantage or benefit or the amount of compensation so determined shall be recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `82-C. Constitution of Authority.-For the purposes of determining the extent of advantage or benefit or the value thereof or the amount of compensation under section 82-B, the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute, as and when necessary, an Authority consisting of one or more members having such qualification and experience and on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed and where the Authority consists of more than one member, one of them may be appointed as Chairperson thereof.`
  line
  line `82-D. Powers of the Authority.-(1) The Authority shall, for purposes of holding inquiry for determining the extent of advantage or benefit or value thereof or the amount of compensation, as the case may be, under section 82-B, have all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 in respect of the following matters, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person or witness and examining him on oath or solemn affirmation;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery or production of any document relating to the subject matter of inquiry;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof relating to the subject matter of inquiry from any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses, documents or other books of accounts relating to the subject matter of inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall also have power to issue a commission to such person as it considers fit for local investigation which may be requisite or proper for the purpose of elucidating any matter which is the subject matter of inquiry or of ascertaining the market value of any property.`
  line
  line `(3) The person directed to execute a commission for any purpose under this section shall have all the powers of a commissioner appointed by a Civil Court in pursuance of the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall have the power to pass such orders as it thinks fit for the seizure, attachment,`
  line `management, preservation, interim custody or sale of any forest produce or timber (wherever it may be in the State) which may be the subject matter of proceedings before it including the appointment of a receiver for any of the aforesaid purposes.`
  line
  line `82-E. Restriction on alienation.-(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force,-`
  line
  line `(a) where at any stage of the inquiry, the Authority is satisfied by affidavit or otherwise that a person liable to restore any advantage or benefit or to pay compensation in lieu thereof under any transaction or lease referred to in section 82-B, is likely to alienate his movable or immovable property with intent to evade payment or to defeat the recovery, of the advantage or benefit or the value thereof or the amount of compensation, that may be determined by him, it may by order in writing direct that such person shall not alienate his movable and immovable property or such portion thereof, as it may specify in the order, during the pendency of the inquiry;`
  line
  line `(b) any alienation of property made in contravention of any order or direction issued under clause (a) shall be void, and no transferee of such property shall be deemed to have acquired any right, title or interest therein.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this section "alienation" includes mortgage, sale, gift, bequest, benami transaction, family settlement or any other mode of transfer of any right, title or interest in the property.`
  line
  line `(2) For removal of doubts it is hereby declared that restrictions imposed under this section on the rights conferred by clause (1) of article 19 of the Constitution of India shall be deemed to be reasonable restrictions.`
  line
  line `82-F. Procedure to be followed by the Authority.--(1) The Authority shall, subject to any rules made by the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir in this behalf, have power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of or connected with the discharge of its functions, in consonance with the principles of natural justice.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties shall have a right of being represented by counsel.`
  line
  line `82-G. Appeal.-(1) Any person aggrieved by a final order of the Authority, determining the extent of advantage or benefit or value thereof or the amount of compensation under section 82-B, may, within thirty days of the date of the order, file an appeal against such order before the High Court and every such appeal shall be heard by a Division Bench of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) No other order of the Authority shall be appealable.`
  line
  line `(3) The order of the Authority shall, subject to the decision of the High Court under sub-section (1) in appeal, be final and shall be deemed to be a certificate within the meaning of section 90 of the Jammu and Kashmir Land Revenue Act, 1996.`
  line
  line `(4) No further appeal shall lie against the decision of the High Court.`
  line
  line `82-H. Exclusion of jurisdiction of Civil Court. No Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or other proceeding in respect of any matter which the Authority has taken cognizance of under section 82-B.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Substituted of section 82--For section 82 of the principal Act, the following section shall be,`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"82. Recovery of money due to State Government.--All money, other than fines, payable to`
  line `the State Government under this Act or under any rule made thereunder or on account of the price of`
  line `any forest produce or any agricultural crop grown on land owned by the State Government in a`
  line `reserved or protected forest or under any contract relating to forest produce or said agricultural crop,`
  line `including any sum recoverable thereunder for breach thereof, or in consequence of its cancellation, or`
  line `under the terms of a notice relating to the sale of such agricultural crop or other forest produce by`
  line `auction or by invitation of tenders issued by or under the authority of a Forest Officer and all`
  line `compensation awarded to the State Government under this Act, may, if not paid when due, be`
  line `recovered, under the law for the time being in force, as if it were an arrear of land revenue."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2001, s. 20]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 82.--For section 82 of the principal act the following sections shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"82. Recovery of money due to State Government.--All money, other than fines, payable to the`
  line `State Government under this Act or under this Act or under any rule made thereunder or on account`
  line `of the price of any forest produce or any agricultural crop grown on land owned by the state`
  line `Government in a reserved or protected forest or under any contract relating to forest produce or said`
  line `agricultural crop, including any sum recoverable thereunder for breach thereof, or in consequence of`
  line `its cancellation, or under the terms of a notice relating to the sale of such agricultural crop or other`
  line `forest produce by auction or by invitation of tenders issued by or under the authority of a Forest`
  line `Officer and all compensation awarded to the state Government under this Act, may, if not paid when`
  line `due, be recovered, under the law for the time being in force, as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarkhand Act 10 of 2002, s. 19]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82 of Act XVI of 1927.--In section 82 of the principal Act, after the words`
  line `"such produce", the words and figures "or on account of compensation or value of property agreed to be`
  line `paid under section 68" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act VI of 1961, s. 16]`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (31944)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 84
  title `Lien on forest-produce for such money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31944&sectionno=83&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any such money is payable for or in respect`
  line `of any forest-produce, the amount thereof shall be deemed to be a first charge on such produce, and such`
  line `produce may be taken possession of by a Forest-officer until such amount has been paid.`
  line
  line `(2) If such amount is not paid when due, the Forest-officer may sell such produce by public auction,`
  line `and the proceeds of the sale shall be applied first in discharging such amount.`
  line
  line `(3) The surplus, if any, if not claimed within two months from the date of the sale by the person`
  line `entitled thereto, shall be forfeited to [Government].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 83A. -- After section 83, insert the following section, namely:--`
  line
  line `83A. Restriction on alienation.(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Transfer of Property Act 1882, or in any other law for the time being in force, no property offered by a forest lessee or by any other person on behalf of a forest lessee, as security for payment of royalty, interest, compensation, penalty or any other amount chargeable from the forest lessee, under any lease deed, bond or instrument shall be alienated without the previous permission of the Government of Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir, till such time as the Chief Conservator of Forests certifies that such forest lessee has duly performed all the obligations devolving upon him under such lease deed, bond or instrument.`
  line
  line `(2) Any alienation of property made in contravention of sub-section (1) shall be void, and no transferee of such property shall be deemed to have acquired any right, title or interest therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Any amount of royalty, interest, compensation or penalty or any other sum falling due from a forest lessee under any lease deed, bond or instrument shall be recoverable as arrears of land revenue in accordance with the law for the time being in force, from the property offered by him or on his behalf as security and from any other movable or immovable property owned by the forest lessee.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,`
  line
  line `(a) "alienation" includes sale, gift, exchange, bequest, mortgage, benami transaction, family settlement or any other mode of transfer of any right, title or interest therein or creation of any encumbrance threreon;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "forest lessee" shall be construed to mean a person in whose favour a right to convert and remove forest produce from any forest has been granted under any lease deed, bond or instrument.`
  line
  line `(4) For removal of doubts it is hereby declared that restriction imposed under this section on the rights conferred by clause (1) of article 19 of the Constitution of India shall be deemed to be reasonable restrictions.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (31945)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 85
  title `Land required under this Act to be deemed to be needed for a public purpose under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31945&sectionno=84&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to the State Government that any land is required for`
  line `any of the purposes of this Act, such land shall be deemed to be needed for a public purpose within the`
  line `meaning of section 4 of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 84A.-After section 84, insert the following section, namely:-`
  line
  line `84A. Application of the Act to land.- The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that any of the provisions of this Act shall apply to any land which is the property of the Government of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or the Central Government, and thereupon such provisions shall apply to such land accordingly.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (31946)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 86
  title `Recovery of penalties due under bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217&sectionId=31946&sectionno=85&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00013_192716_1523350029217
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `When any person, in accordance with any provision of`
  line `this Act, or in compliance with any rule made thereunder, binds himself by any bond or instrument to`
  line `perform any duty or act, or covenants by any bond or instrument that he, or that he and his servants and`
  line `agents will abstain from any act, the whole sum mentioned in such bond or instrument as the amount to`
  line `be paid in case of a breach of the conditions thereof may, notwithstanding anything in section 74 of the`
  line `Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), be recovered from him in case of such breach as if it were an`
  line `arrear of land-revenue.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 85 of Act XVI of 1927.--Section 85 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, shall be`
  line `renumbered, as sub-section (1) of that section, and after sub-section (1) so renumbered the following subsection shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) If any question arises--`
  line
  line `(a) whether there has been a breach of any of the conditions of such bond or instrument,`
  line
  line `(b) as to the sum to be paid for such breach,`
  line
  line `(c) as to the person or persons liable to pay such sum,`
  line `the question shall be referred to and, after giving notice to the person concerned and after considering`
  line `his objections (if any), be decided by an officer, not below the rank of a Divisional Forest Officer,`
  line `authorized by the Government in this behalf. The person aggrieved by the decision of such officer may,`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of such decision, appeal to the State Government or such other`
  line `appellate authority as the State Government may appoint in this behalf. The decision of such officer,`
  line `subject to an appeal to the appellate authority, and the decision of the appellate authority on such appeal,`
  line `shall be final."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act X of 1956, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 85 of Act XVI of 1927.--In sub-section (2) of section 85 of the Indian Forest`
  line `act, 1927 (XVI of 1927), for the words "Divisional Forest Officer" the words "Sub-Divisional Forest`
  line `Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVI of 1957, s. 2]`
